Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.85,0:00:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,一切有关堕胎的事都是罪恶的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Everything involved in an abortion is sin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,它是错误，我真的相信这是邪恶\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it's wrong, I actually believe it's evil{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.38,0:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，邪恶的东西没有价值\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so there's no value in things that are evil{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,当孩子的肢体被扯碎时，他甚至还活着\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The child is ripped limb from limb while it's still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.17,0:00:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他的心脏还在跳动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}while his heart is still beating{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.16,0:00:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我是一个母亲\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm a mother{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.29,0:00:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得怀孕很美好，我爱我的孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I loved my pregnancies. I love my children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.68,0:00:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在是四个孩子的祖母\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm now a grandmother of four{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.50,0:00:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,当一个女人怀孕时…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When a woman becomes pregnant{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:57.46,自定义,,0,0,0,,德克萨斯州   国会议员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.69,0:00:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,她把自己身体的一部分给了另一个人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}she loses a part of herself to someone else{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.17,0:01:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,大多数人都期待这个经历，因为这很美好\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Most of us want that, because it's beautiful{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.00,0:01:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,但并非每个人都这样\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is not that way for everyone{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.67,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以自以为是地坐在这里\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We can sit here self-righteously
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.73,0:01:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,总是认为自己了解每一个人，但并非如此\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and decide that we always know best for every person, but we do not{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.61,0:01:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,没有理由一遍又一遍地回到这里\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There's no reason to come back here, session after session,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.65,0:01:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,让堕胎变得越来越困难，让妇女们回到非法堕胎的阴影中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and make it more and more difficult and drive women back into the shadows of illegal abortions,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.65,0:01:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这就是后果，她们无力去阻止它发生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because it's exactly what this will do. They will not stop having them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,她们总是堕胎，我们总是堕胎，妇女总是堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They've always had abortions. We've always had abortions. Women always had abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.73,0:01:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,而这将永远是我们的追求\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that will always be something that will be sought{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.02,0:01:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们想禁止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you want to stop abortions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.93,0:01:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那就帮我阻止意外怀孕吧\N{\fnarial\fs12\}then help me stop unwanted pregnancies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.08,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,修正案议程异议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Question occurs on the adoption of the amendment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.09,0:01:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,议员克里克，赞成票\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Representative Klick voting aye{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.44,0:01:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,议员奥利佛森，赞成票\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Representative Oliverson voting aye{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,所有成员都投票了吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Have all members voted?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.98,0:01:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,92票赞成，42票反对，修正案通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There being 92 ayes and 42 nays, the amendment is adopted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.37,0:02:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一项对堕胎施加更多限制的法案已在立法机关获得通过…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}A bill has moved forward in the legislature, placing more restrictions on abortion…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.17,0:02:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们正在努力达成…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They're trying to get something in place…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.18,0:02:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}德克萨斯州将出台新的堕胎规定{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Texas will have new abortion regulations{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.74,0:02:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，堕胎的机会越来越少\N{\fnarial\fs12\}so that there's less and less opportunity to have an abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.64,0:02:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,也许，直到根本毫无选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}till, perhaps, there is no option at all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.41,0:02:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在“罗诉韦德案”之前，我还很年轻，当时堕胎是非法的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I was a young woman prior to Roe v. Wade, when abortion was illegal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.79,0:02:29.54,自定义,,0,0,0,,（生孩子是你的主要职责吗？）
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道那段时期有多困难\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I know the difficulties of that period of time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.21,0:02:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这种倒退的想法让我无法忍受\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The idea that we would go back to that was just unbearable to me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.14,0:02:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,法案禁止了一种最常见的妊娠中期堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The bill banned one of the most common types of second-trimester abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.89,0:02:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,该法案禁止了一项特定程序\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This bill prohibits one specific procedure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.92,0:02:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们从一开始就明确表示\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But we made it very clear from the beginning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.32,0:02:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,立法的重点必须是制止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the legislative priority needs to be something that will stop abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.18,0:02:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,立法的重点应该是揭露堕胎的真相\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The legislative priority needs to be something that reveals the truth about abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,其首要任务是让我们更接近推翻“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and the legislative priority needs to be something that will get us closer to overturning Roe v. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我的目标是，让堕胎在任何阶段都成为过去\N{\fnarial\fs12\}My goal is to make abortion at any stage a thing of the paSt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这个法案实际上保护了肯塔基州超过20周的人类生命\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This bill actually protects human life beyond 20 weeks here in the Commonwealth of Kentucky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我是亲生命派，我坚信…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I am pro-life, and I very strongly believe that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.94,0:03:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须提倡生命，捍卫生命……\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we must promote life, defend life…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我的目标是，在密西西比州终止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}My goal is to end abortion in Mississippi{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.44,0:03:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在美国，堕胎的权利正在逐渐丧失\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There is a steady chipping away of the right to abortion in America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这个国家的有些地方，就像“罗诉韦德案”从来没发生过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There are places in the country, it's as if Roe versus Wade never happened{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.88,0:03:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天，最高法院将堕胎合法化…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Supreme Court today legalized abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,自2010年以来，国家已经通过了300项堕胎限制\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Since 2010, 300 abortion restrictions have been passed in this country,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我想很多人都没有意识到，堕胎是多么受限\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I think many people are unaware of how restricted abortion has become{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.80,0:03:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党是“亲生命党”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Republican Party's the party of life,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,因为人们想要生命，不想要死亡\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because people want life, they don't want death{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.29,0:04:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们想终止堕胎，如果我们要通过不断立法来实现\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We want to end abortion. If we're gonna do it through continuous legislation,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.73,0:04:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那么我们就会一次又一次地反复进行，直到获胜\N{\fnarial\fs12\}then we're gonna go back again and again and again, until we win{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,片名：推翻罗诉韦德案
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:29.10,自定义,,0,0,0,,密苏里州
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我的感觉是，当时密苏里州堕胎问题的氛围相当紧张…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think the feeling was that with the climate as pretty tense around the abortion issue in Missouri…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,过去密苏里有几个地方是可以堕胎的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Missouri used to have several places where you could get an abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在过去的十年里\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but over the last decade,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.65,0:04:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,越来越多的法律法规被通过…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}more and more laws and regulations have been passed…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}计划生育协会证实，哥伦比亚诊所已经停止堕胎…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood confirmed the Columbia clinic has stopped performing abortions…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.79,0:04:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,正因为如此，提供这种服务变得越来越难\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and because of that, it becomes harder and harder to provide that care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.39,0:04:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}周四是诊所接受妇女堕胎的最后一天{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Thursday was the last day women could have an abortion at the clinic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.43,0:04:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,现在密苏里州只有一家堕胎诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And now there's just one abortion clinic in Missouri{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.86,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,她是那个做堕胎手术的女士\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She's the lady that does the abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.06,0:05:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,圣路易斯计划生育处\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Planned Parenthood in Saint Louis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,神爱世人…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}God does love you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,考虑好你今天要做的事，请不要这么做\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Please, think about what you're doing today and not do that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.81,0:05:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这些婴儿今天不想死，科琳\N{\fnarial\fs12\}These babies don't want to die today, Colleen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.50,0:05:23.67,自定义,,0,0,0,,科琳•麦克尼古拉斯   妇科医生
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.37,0:05:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始的时候\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When I started out,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.02,0:05:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为堕胎只是惯例的一部分，你知道\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I thought abortion would just be part of my practice; that, you know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就像人们需要子宫切除一样，人们需要堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}just like people need hysterectomies, people need abortions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我会照顾那些需要帮助的病人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I will take care of my patients who need those{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.78,0:05:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我意识到，在保守的州，想堕胎非常困难\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But I realize that in conservative states it can be very hard to get an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我成了一名专注于堕胎服务的医生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so I became a physician who really focuses on abortion care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.94,0:05:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我住在圣路易斯，但是…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I live in Saint Louis, but{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.86,0:05:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,四周之中有三周我都要跑去其他地方\N{\fnarial\fs12\}three out of four weeks, I'm traveling somewhere{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,周一周二可能在俄克拉荷马\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it might be Monday and Tuesday in Oklahoma,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,周五周六回到圣路易斯\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Friday and Saturday back to St. Louis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来周一在威奇托…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Then the following Monday in Wichita,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:03.55,自定义,,0,0,0,,威奇托（堪萨斯州）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.61,0:05:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我提供堕胎服务的四个地方之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}which is one of the four places where I provide abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.44,0:06:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们以杀人为生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They kill people for a living here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.86,0:06:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能袖手旁观，听之任之\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We cannot stand by and say, "Well, we're just gonna let that happen",{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,或者说这是女人的选择，等等\N{\fnarial\fs12\}or it's the woman's choice and so on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我对我们正在做的事情很高兴，我将继续做下去，我们会赢\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm happy with what we're doing, and I'm gonna continue doing it. And we're gonna win{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.92,0:06:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我是特朗普的长期支持者，我们会获胜的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm a big-time Trump supporter, and we're gonna win this{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,时候已到，真相即将大白\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's…The time is coming. The truth is coming out, that's what's happening{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，已经有些人来问过我\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Well, I've had these people out here ask me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:30.16,自定义,,0,0,0,,诊所保安
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.88,0:06:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我对堕胎本身的想法和意见是什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}what my thoughts and opinions of abortion itself is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我给了他们同样的答案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I give 'em the same answer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“我认为”，我一直如此\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"My opinion" I keep it that way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我来这的主要原因是她，在旗杆上飘着的国旗\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The main reason I'm here is that girl, that flies up there on that flagpole{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.32,0:06:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我最为反感这些人的是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What I have against these people more than anything{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.90,0:06:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他们一直试图把自己的宗教强加给别人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is that they keep trying to push their religion up on someone else{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,而这个国家本该是有宗教自由的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in a nation that's supposed to have religious freedom{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.28,0:06:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，你可以想任何你想要的东西\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, you can think whatever you want about it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但是，在美国\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But, in America,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.68,0:07:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,每四个妇女中会有一人有过堕胎的经历\N{\fnarial\fs12\}one in four women will have an abortion in their life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,所以对我来说，堕胎只是基本的医疗保健\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, to me, abortion is just basic health care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.70,0:07:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要终止妊娠，好吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're gonna remove the pregnancy, okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当我想到这个事已经变得如此政治化…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when I think about how politicized this has become…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.37,0:07:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我想知道，这到底是怎么发生的？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I wonder, you know, well, how did this happen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.40,0:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}做过很多自我反省后，我真诚地认为{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In all the soul-searching I have done, I sincerely feel{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.97,0:07:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果现在这样做了…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that if they do it now…that they are only{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.65,0:07:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就只是相当于一团组织脱离了我…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}disengaging from me…a kind of mass of tissue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.34,0:07:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在20世纪60年代早期，堕胎是非法的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In the early 1960s, abortion was illegal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.77,0:07:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,有个叫雪莉•芬克班的女人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there was a woman named Sherri Finkbine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.88,0:07:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,她是凤凰台一个儿童电视节目的主持人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She was a children's television hostess in Phoenix{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:51.85,自定义,,0,0,0,,琳达•格林豪斯    堕胎史学家
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.02,0:07:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,雪莉小姐，她有四个孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Miss Sherri, she had four children,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.13,0:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,她怀了一个非常想要的孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and she was pregnant with a much-wanted baby{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:01.89,自定义,,0,0,0,,（关于沙利多胺的重大警告）
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.96,0:08:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是她服用了一种叫做沙利多胺的药物\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But she had taken this drug called thalidomide{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:06.54,自定义,,0,0,0,,（沙利多胺首例致死事件，新生儿缺少四肢）
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,她去看医生时问到，“这是怎么回事？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And she went to her doctor and said, "What about this?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他说，“我建议你堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And he said, "I recommend that you have an abortion"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“我可以在医院里为你安排一次堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}He said, "I can arrange an abortion for you in the hospital here"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.46,0:08:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,医院做的一些所谓“治疗性堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Hospitals did some what they called "therapeutic abortions"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,只是为了挽救妇女的生命\N{\fnarial\fs12\}only to save the life of women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:25.81,自定义,,0,0,0,,汤姆•戴维斯   牧师（基督联合教会）
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但是如果医生想要帮助这个女人，他会把这个解释得很宽泛\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But if the doctor wanted to help the woman out, he would interpret that very broadly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,女人可能会说：“我要自杀了”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The woman might say, "I'm gonna kill myself"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.45,0:08:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他会说，“她的生命危在旦夕”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Then he could say, "Her life is at stake"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,如果进行治疗性堕胎，通常是根据\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If therapeutic abortion is done, it's usually done on the basis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.09,0:08:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,患者的精神和情感障碍进行的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}of the mental and emotional disturbance to the patient{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.86,0:08:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,女性必须在男性医生组成委员会面前，请求堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Women had to go before a committee of male doctors to ask for an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.78,0:08:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,女性通常受到非常恶劣的对待，比如\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And women were often treated very badly. Like,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.97,0:08:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“好吧，我们会为你堕胎，如果你能同意绝育的话”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Well, we'll do the abortion for you, but if you agree to be sterilized"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,这是十分平常的程序\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a common procedure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.37,0:08:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“我们不想收拾你的烂摊子”，他们会如此说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"We don't want to clean up your mess", they would say things like that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果你是一个富有的白人女性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But if you were a wealthy white woman,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.30,0:09:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你也许能找到办法得以手术\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you could probably find a way to get access to the procedure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这将被称为“治疗性堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it would be called a therapeutic abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,雪莉在医院预约了堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Sherri had an appointment at the hospital for the abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,她觉得自己有义务让别人知道这件事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And she felt that she had an obligation to let this be known{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.21,0:09:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这样其他处于同样处境的女性也会有同样的选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}so that other women in the same position would have the same option{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,而一旦这些话在当地报纸上传开了…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But once the word kind of got out into the local newspaper, you know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,医院却说，“不，我们不能给你堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the hospital said, "Oh, no, we can't give you an abortion"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,她在国内找不到任何堕胎的地方，只能去了瑞典\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She couldn't find a place for an abortion any place in the country. She had to go to Sweden{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.23,0:09:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我只想做对自己和我的家庭都正确的事情{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I just want to do what's right for myself and my family,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我并不会对那些极其反对此事的人感到抱歉{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I don't feel bitter towards people who oppose this religiously{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为我们做的对，我想强调一下{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think we're doing the right thing. I'd like to really emphasize{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.66,0:09:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们不是在为别人做决定{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're not making a decision for other people{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.26,0:09:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这对我们的家庭来说，在特殊情况下这是正确选择{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is right for our family and in our particular case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:54.75,自定义,,0,0,0,,（堕胎与安乐死的道德问题）
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这变成了一个大事件，上了生活杂志\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This became a big story. It was in Life magazine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.76,0:09:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得当我小的时候，边读边想\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I remember as a very young kid reading it and thinking,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.42,0:10:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“这些是什么东西？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Hmm, what's this about?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:04.46,自定义,,0,0,0,,（堕胎——未出世的生命应该死吗？）
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.07,0:10:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，它十分受人瞩目\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, it focused people's attention{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.94,0:10:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你怀孕了，但不想生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you were pregnant and did not want to be,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.29,0:10:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在五、六十年代，你很少有选择的余地\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in the '50s and '60s, you had very few options{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.04,0:10:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，如果你不想要一个孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, if you didn't want to have a child,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.77,0:10:28.37,自定义,,0,0,0,,葛劳利亚•斯泰纳姆   女权活动家
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,要么你很幸运，有个肯帮助你的家庭医生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}either you were lucky enough to have a family doctor who would help you,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,要么有足够的钱，去波多黎各或其他国家\N{\fnarial\fs12\}or to have enough money to go to Puerto Rico or some other country,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里你可以堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}where you could get an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.67,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,大学毕业后，我怀孕了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}After I graduated from college, I was pregnant{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.95,0:10:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时在英国，不知该怎么办，十分害怕\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I was in England. I didn't know what to do and was terrified{\r} 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.65,0:10:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我在伦敦的电话簿里找到了一个医生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I found a doctor in the phone book in London{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他说，“答应我两件事”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And he said, "Promise me two things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“第一，别把我的名字告诉任何人”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}One, you will not tell anyone my name{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“第二，你可以做你想做的事”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And two, you will do what you want to do with your life"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,直到今天我都很感激他\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I'm grateful to him to this day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.57,0:11:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我对堕胎一无所知\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I didn't know anything about abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.46,0:11:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,直到1966年，我成了斯基德莫尔学院的牧师\N{\fnarial\fs12\}until I became the chaplain at Skidmore College in 1966{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.20,0:11:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,有一次我告诉我妻子，“你知道，1400个年轻女人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I told my wife at one point, I said, "You know, 1,400 young women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.33,0:11:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,她们能有什么问题？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What kind of problems could they have?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,她说，“你真是笨蛋，你会发现的”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And she said, "You're a dope. You're gonna find out"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那些怀了孕但不想告诉家人的学生，就会来找我\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Students who were pregnant, but didn't want to tell their families, would come to me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.52,0:11:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我把这个学生送到斯科纳特迪的一个医生那里\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I'd send the student to a doctor in Schenectady,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.69,0:11:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他一直认为堕胎是有必要的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who always found it necessary to do an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我学到的，我不仅仅是一个牧师\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that's how I learned that I wasn't just a chaplain{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.57,0:11:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白了我是一名堕胎顾问\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I learned I was an abortion counselor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,还有许多大学牧师在全国各地做着同样的事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There were many other college chaplains doing the same thing around the country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.27,0:11:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这里是神职人员怀孕问题咨询服务中心{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is the Clergy Consultation Service on problem pregnancy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,第一个公共组织是神职人员咨询服务\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The first public organized group was the Clergy Consultation Service{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.18,0:11:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,包括19位新教牧师和两个犹太拉比\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This was 19 Protestant ministers and two Jewish rabbis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.62,0:11:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}本周的牧师咨询是…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Clergymen counseling this week are Reverend…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.56,0:12:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我也是其中之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I was a part of that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不会问她们为什么要堕胎，这与我们无关\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We would not ask them why they were having the abortion. That was not our business{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.91,0:12:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但是大多数女人都想谈论这个话题，她们想告诉我为什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But most of the women wanted to talk about it. They wanted to tell me why{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,所以对于一个年轻的男牧师，这是一次了解女性生活的教育\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so it was quite an education for a young male minister into the lives of women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们进了这间公寓，那里又黑又暗{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We went into this apartment, and it was dark, dingy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.41,0:12:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他道歉说，“我很抱歉，你必须像个罪犯一样被对待”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}He apologized. He said, "I'm sorry you have to be treated like a criminal"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.68,0:12:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这位24岁的女孩，在不到一小时前进行了非法堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This 24-year-old girl had an illegal abortion less than an hour ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.53,0:12:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}据估计，管控堕胎的法律每年被违反100万次{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The laws which govern abortion are broken an estimated one million times a year{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管她们遭受了极大的侮辱\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Even though they suffered great indignity,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,富有的女性通常有一种安全的方法来结束意外怀孕\N{\fnarial\fs12\}wealthy women often had a safe way of ending an unintended pregnancy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:52.16,自定义,,0,0,0,,菲•沃特莱顿    计划生育协会前主席
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但在哈莱姆医院的临床培训期间\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But during my clinical training at Harlem Hospital, I really was thruSt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的被推入了一个满是来自贫困家庭的妇女的环境\N{\fnarial\fs12\}into an environment where women were from a very poor and deprived background{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.61,0:13:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,后来我发现，非洲裔美国妇女的贫困程度尤其严重\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then I saw that African-American women who were disproportionately poor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.02,0:13:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她们是当时限制性政策最直接的受害者\N{\fnarial\fs12\} were the most directly hurt by the restrictive policies of the time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,有一些非常悲惨的案例\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There were some pretty sad cases of women attempting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.86,0:13:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,妇女试图自己终止妊娠\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to terminate their pregnancies themselves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.56,0:13:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}事实令人震惊{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The facts are astonishing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每年有35万名女性罹患并发症{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}350,000 women a year suffer complications{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中5000名妇女死亡{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}5,000 of these women die{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.95,0:13:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,有许多惊恐的妇女，她们使用衣架…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There were many terrified women who were using coat hangers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.21,0:13:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,和刀子，把自己摔下楼梯…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and knives and throwing themselves down stairs{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,而去找非法堕胎医生通常也不安全\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And going to an illegal abortion doctor was often unsafe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.47,0:13:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它只是一个衣架，一个普通的衣架{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was just a piece of hanger, an ordinary hanger{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不是一整个的，只是一片{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not a whole one, Just a piece{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.66,0:13:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,当你堕胎时，你不得不花费700美元\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When you have an abortion, you have to pay $700{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.45,0:13:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,通过这个隐秘的行动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to go through this cloak-and-dagger business{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,找一个愿意把衣架塞进你身体的家伙\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to find you some guy who's willing to stick a hanger up you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说有个会议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I heard that there was a meeting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.09,0:14:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它是在村里的一个教堂举行的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was being held in a church in the Village{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我要说的是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What I'm talking about,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,看看你的邻居，她八成堕过胎了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}more than likely, look at your neighbor. She had an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.98,0:14:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,而且，你知道，女人只是站出来讲述她们的故事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And, you know, women just got up and told their stories{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.82,0:14:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那些人给了我一笔交易：{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Those men offered me a deal:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果我不做绝育，那就不能给我堕胎…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I couldn't have an abortion if I wasn't sterilized…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.77,0:14:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的一生中，从来没有听到有女人说过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I had never, ever in my life heard women telling the truth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,这些事只发生在女人身上的真相\N{\fnarial\fs12\}about something that only happened to women,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.07,0:14:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,并且说，“事情不该是这样，我们必须改变它”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and saying, "This doesn't have to be this way. We have to change it"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为法律是为了让那个女人安分守己而制定的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}'Cause the laws are made to keep that woman in her place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,突然间，你知道，那是伟大的灵光乍现\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And suddenly, you know, that was a great "aha" You know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.68,0:14:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我想，“好吧，我有过这样的经历\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I thought, "Okay, I had this experience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.57,0:14:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,三分之一的美国女性有过这样的经历\N{\fnarial\fs12\}One in three American women has had this experience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么，为什么它是非法的和危险的？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Why, why is it illegal and dangerous?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这是揭开序幕的开始\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That was kind of the beginning of the unraveling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你要隐瞒什么吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You got something to hide?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.01,0:15:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不后悔我做了这件事，我还会再做的，我认为应该合法化{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm not sorry I did it and I would do it again, and I think it should be legalized{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,问题是生育自由\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The issue is reproductive freedom,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.85,0:15:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,意味着有生孩子的权利，同样也有不生孩子的权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and that means the right to have children, as well as the right not to have children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.66,0:15:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,一些真正意义深远的事情正在发生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Something really profound is happening{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,主要是女人已经掌握了这个游戏\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Mainly that women have caught onto the game{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还没有完全了解它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We don't know it completely yet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，我们还没有真正发现我们被压迫的全部结构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, we haven't really discovered the total anatomy of our oppression{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.26,0:15:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,以及他们对我们做了什么，但我们知道它正在发生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and of what they've been doing to us. But we do know that it's happening{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.74,0:15:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经开始了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're on to it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.96,0:15:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自由选择！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Free choice!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是一场战斗，我们不会放弃\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is going to be a battle, and we will not give up{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,妇女实现堕胎的权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}on the right of a woman to achieve abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.33,0:15:37.96,自定义,,0,0,0,,埃莉诺•霍尔姆斯•诺顿    国会议员
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,早期女权主义者…立即意识到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Early feminists… understood immediately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.18,0:15:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎是女权主义和妇女权利的核心问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that abortion was a central issue of feminism and to women's rights{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.53,0:15:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们要什么？\N- 自由选择！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- What do we want?   - Free choice!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.65,0:15:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么时候要？\N- 现在！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- When do you want it?  - Now!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果连自己的身体都不能控制，还能要求什么权利？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you didn't have control over your own body, what kind of right could you ask for?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.19,0:15:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个政治问题，国家意味着控制我们的身体\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is a political issue, and the state means to control our bodies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.92,0:16:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们生育士兵，我们生育工人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We produce the soldiers, we produce the workers,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.56,0:16:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而他们害怕失去这种控制\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and they fear the loss of that control{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,控制自己的身体，是民主的基础\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's the basis of democracy that you control your own body{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这是等级制度和极权制度所没有的基础\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it's the basis of hierarchy and totalitarian regimes that you don't{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:18.65,自定义,,0,0,0,,华盛顿D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.05,0:16:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,安全的合法堕胎对我们来说是不可用的——\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Safe legal abortions are not available to our--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.31,0:16:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，请坐下来，否则请离开——\N{\fnarial\fs12\}All right{\r} Will you please sit down or be removed--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不，我们不会坐下，你为什么不——\N{\fnarial\fs12\}No, we aren't gonna sit down. Why don't you--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.05,0:16:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,一个女人怀孕了，她被当作罪犯对待\N{\fnarial\fs12\}A woman gets pregnant and she's treated like a criminal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她不能堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She can't get an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.76,0:16:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,不管她愿不愿意，她都必须生下那个孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She has to go through having that child, whether she wants it or not{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.24,0:16:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在法院介入堕胎问题之前\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Before the courts got involved in the abortion issue,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.80,0:16:34.80,自定义,,0,0,0,,（女性团体对改革施压）
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.42,0:16:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这个问题看起来好像会在政治上得到解决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}it looked as if the matter would be settled in politics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天，加州通过了一项新的自由堕胎法{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}California passed a new liberalized abortion law today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,加州州长罗纳德•里根实际上签署了一项改革法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}California Governor Ronald Reagan actually signed a reform bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.34,0:16:57.29,自定义,,0,0,0,,加利弗尼亚治疗性堕胎法案
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.04,0:17:03.37,自定义,,0,0,0,,（里根签署历史性的堕胎法案）
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为有件事人们今天没有意识到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think one thing that people don't realize today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:17:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党曾经是支持堕胎的政党\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is that it was the Republican Party that was the pro-choice party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.94,0:17:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有些共和党人执政的州，都通过了堕胎改革法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there were states with Republican governors who passed abortion reforms{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,然后纽约完全废除了19世纪的旧堕胎法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then New York totally repealed the old 19th-century abortion law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.09,0:17:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…这是全国范围内最具影响力的堕胎控制法案之一{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…one of the nation's most sweeping abortion control bills{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.84,0:17:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,纽约的法律规定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The New York law said{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你愿意，你可以在孕期的两三个月内堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you can have an abortion throughout the first two trimesters just if you wanted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你无需给出任何理由，这只是你的选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You don't have to give a reason or anything. It's your choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,1970年7月1日\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And on July 1st, 1970,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.81,0:17:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,美国第一家合法堕胎诊所，是由纽约市的神职人员开设的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the first legal abortion clinic in America was opened by the clergy of New York City{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这家诊所在13个月内每天能做一百多次堕胎手术\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that clinic did over a hundred abortions a day for 13 months,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,直到其他诊所成立\N{\fnarial\fs12\}until other clinics had formed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.45,0:17:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是激进的第一步\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is the first radical step{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.44,0:17:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这引起了天主教会的注意\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that set off the Catholic Church{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.06,0:17:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我已把生与死摆在你面前\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I have set before you life and death{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:02.79,自定义,,0,0,0,,特恩斯•库克   纽约教区红衣主教
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，选择生命吧\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Therefore, choose life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,未出生的孩子没有选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The unborn child has no choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个问题上，教堂给你提供了你所需要的帮助吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Does the Catholic Church give you as much help as you need in this issue?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.74,0:18:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,天主教会在反对堕胎方面非常有策略\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Catholic Church was very strategic in its opposition to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.82,0:18:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他们设立了“生命权利委员会”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They set up the Right to Life committee,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.95,0:18:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,红衣主教和教会大力反对\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and the cardinal and the church pushed back vigorously{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.94,0:18:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在纽约，合法堕胎已经夺去了近50万的无辜生命\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Legal abortion in New York has already claimed almost a half million innocent lives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.94,0:18:35.59,自定义,,0,0,0,,（堕胎自由计划受到抨击）
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.94,0:18:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,纽约州的堕胎法案在立法机构被提了出来\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the New York abortion law came up in the legislature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…打掉子宫里的人类胎儿，你应该感到恶心！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…to abort a human fetus in the womb, you oughta get sick to your stomach!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.36,0:18:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在纽约有很多天主教徒选民\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There were a lot of Catholic voters in New York,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:45.21,自定义,,0,0,0,,谭雅•梅利奇   共和党员（纽约）
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.74,0:18:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,教会说：“我们反对堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and the church was saying, "We're against abortion"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.18,0:18:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们是一个有着犹太基督教传统的国家{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Ours is a nation with a Judeo-Christian heritage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.53,0:18:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党控制了立法机构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Republicans were in control of the legislature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.36,0:18:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些都不能证明堕胎是正当的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}None of this justifies abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.52,0:19:02.97,自定义,,0,0,0,,（议会投票废除自由堕胎法）
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.52,0:19:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他们又在废除堕胎合法化\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And now they were repealing legalized abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我认识的共和党人对税收和庞大的预算感到愤怒\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Republicans I knew got angry about taxes and how big the budget's gonna be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.92,0:19:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为共和党的传统\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think that the traditions of the Republican Party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.68,0:19:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是个人选择自己想要什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}are the traditions of an individual person to choose what he wishes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.81,0:19:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,只要不侵犯他人的利益\N{\fnarial\fs12\}as long as it doesn't infringe upon other people{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.80,0:19:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是相信个人自由的政党\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We were the party that believed in individual liberty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.07,0:19:24.18,自定义,,0,0,0,,尼尔森•洛克菲勒  政府官员（共和党）
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.23,0:19:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,恭喜你\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Congratulations{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,洛克菲勒州长是“亲选择”派的…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Governor Rockefeller was pro-choice…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.37,0:19:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我们觉得，“为什么是国家来告诉妇女\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we felt, "Why should the state be telling women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.93,0:19:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,她们是否可以堕胎？ ”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}whether or not they could have an abortion?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:33.10,自定义,,0,0,0,,（州长否决废除堕胎是不正当的）
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.79,0:19:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,洛克菲勒否决了该法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Rockefeller vetoed the bill…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,而堕胎在纽约是合法的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and abortion stayed legal in New York{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,1972年夏天，有一项盖洛普民意测验\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There was a Gallup poll in the summer of 1972{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.39,0:19:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,要求人们回答这个问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that asked people to answer the question,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.22,0:19:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“你认为堕胎应该是一个女人和她的医生之间的事吗？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Do you believe that abortion should be a matter between a woman and her doctor?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.17,0:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,大约2/3的共和党人同意这个问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Republicans by about two-thirds said yes to that question,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“堕胎应该是留给一个女人和她的医生之间的问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Abortion should be a matter left to a woman and her doctor,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.77,0:20:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是政府”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not the government"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我可能是这个国家最老的堕胎服务提供者了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think I'm probably the oldest provider of abortion services in the country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.37,0:20:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我在1967年第一次堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I did my first abortion in 1967{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,非法堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Illegal abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.47,0:20:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,神职人员协商会打电话来问我\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Clergy Consultation called, and they asked me,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“柯蒂斯，你会考虑做堕胎手术吗？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Curtis, would you consider doing abortions?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.74,0:20:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你有什么问题要和我谈吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Do you have any problems you want to discuss with me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.21,0:20:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是它开始的地方\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, that's where it started{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.06,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我可能会进监狱，可能会失去我的行医执照\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I thought I could go to prison, I could lose my medical license{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.22,0:20:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我从小就信教\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I grew up religious{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.78,0:20:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,在高中的最后一年被任命为牧师\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I became an ordained minister my senior year in high school{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.50,0:21:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为基督教的基本教义是同情和服务\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I think the basic Christian teaching is compassion and service{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.09,0:21:08.03,自定义,,0,0,0,,柯蒂斯•博伊德   妇科医生
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我的头脑，内心，我的手都说要这样做，我可以做出改变\N{\fnarial\fs12\}My head and my heart and my hands said to do this. I can make a difference,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我要冒这个险\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I'm going take the risk{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.01,0:21:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,从那以后，我一直在做这项工作\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I've done this work ever since{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.81,0:21:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在80岁了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm now 80 years old{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.64,0:21:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,80年后，我决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And after 80 years, I've decided{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.34,0:21:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不再换工作了，这就是我的工作\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm not moving on to another career. I think this is it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.52,0:21:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说，仍然有人需要我\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I mean, I'm still needed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:30.45,自定义,,0,0,0,,达拉斯（德克萨斯州）
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.52,0:21:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢您致电西南妇女外科中心\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Thank you for calling the Southwestern Women's Surgery Center{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我是艾丽西娅，需要帮助吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm Alicia. How may I help you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，我明天下午有空\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Okay. I have availability for tomorrow afternoon…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.66,0:21:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,人们一直敦促我，要把平生所学和经历传递下去\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I've been urged by people to pass on what I have learned and experienced{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.44,0:21:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，这就是我正在做的，尽力去教导年轻医生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, that's what I'm doing, trying to teach as many young doctors as I can{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,……仔细地详述……\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…dilate carefully…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.39,0:21:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我的理念是，提供堕胎服务的目的是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}My philosophy is that the goal in providing abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:22:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,帮助妇女为自己和自己的生活做出最佳决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is to assist the woman in making the best decision she can for her and her life…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.45,0:22:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,无论付出什么代价\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in whatever that takes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.78,0:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎争议中最重要的道德问题是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The most important moral question of the abortion debate is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.35,0:22:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,子宫里的是什么？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}what is in the womb?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.69,0:22:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,它是一个人吗？它值得我们的人道关怀和保护吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Is it a person? Does it deserve our moral attention and protection or not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.12,0:22:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,这是最重要的问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That is the most important question{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.72,0:22:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在亲生命运动中，我们被激怒了，因为我们相信\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In the pro-life movement, we're outraged, because we believe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.80,0:22:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,选择性堕胎就是夺走了一个无辜的生命\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that elective abortion is the taking of an innocent human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.81,0:22:28.30,自定义,,0,0,0,,约翰•西沟   德克萨斯州生命权利协会
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.84,0:22:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不公正的行为，我们可以停止，而且需要停止\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That is an act of injustice that we can stop and we need to stop{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.93,0:22:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这是博伊德医生…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- This is Doctor Boyd.   - Dr. Boyd{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.12,0:22:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你有问题，我们希望你能告诉我们\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you have questions, we want you to let us know{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.17,0:22:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会好好照顾你并处理……\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we'll take good care of you and make this{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,妇女继续怀孕，生了孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Women continue a pregnancy and have a baby,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.58,0:22:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,因为当时他们想要个孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because they want a baby at that time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,而她们堕胎，是因为她们有充分的理由\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they have an abortion because they don't want to be pregnant{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,自己不想在那个时候怀孕\N{\fnarial\fs12\}at that time in their life for their own sufficient reasons{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.16,0:22:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,德克萨斯州要求，至少在堕胎前24小时到医院就诊\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The state of Texas requires that you be seen at least 24 hours before your abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.33,0:22:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那么我要给你看这个超声波图\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then I'm gonna show you this sonogram{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.41,0:23:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,大概是五到六周吧？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That looks like between five and six weeks, okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.92,0:23:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,超声波技术是亲生命运动最好的帮手之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Sonogram technology is one of the best friends of the pro-life movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这改变了一代人对女性子宫内发生的事情的看法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is changing a generation's mind about what's going on in the womb of a woman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.26,0:23:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,通常情况下，母亲会把超声波图贴在冰箱上\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is very common for expecting mothers to have sonograms on their fridge{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.67,0:23:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,让孩子们知道那是什么照片，那是他们的兄弟姐妹\N{\fnarial\fs12\}for children to know what that picture is. That is their sibling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.13,0:23:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个很好的工具，我们想要利用它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so this was a great tool that we wanted to tap into and to use,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.66,0:23:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们发现堕胎诊所已经在堕胎前使用了超声波技术\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and we saw that abortion clinics were already using sonogram technology before an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.25,0:23:36.62,自定义,,0,0,0,,（超声波：子宫的窗口）
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.69,0:23:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大家早上好，约翰•西沟和科技公司…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Good morning, everybody. John Seago with tech…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.45,0:23:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我们非常谨慎地思考我们正在做什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We think very deliberately about what are we doing that is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.05,0:23:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是在向挑战“罗诉韦德案”的根本基础迈进一步\N{\fnarial\fs12\}taking a step forward to challenging the very foundations of Roe v. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.80,0:23:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,超声波检查的法案很重要\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the sonogram bill was an important one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.52,0:23:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们一直在推动医生使用它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because we were pushing how much we can require a physician to do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.32,0:23:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，那么德州健康和安全准则第171章要求\N{\fnarial\fs12\}All right. So Chapter 171 of the Texas Health and Safety Code require that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.32,0:23:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在你手术前24小时向你提供以下信息…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I provide you with this information at least 24 hours prior to your procedure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.36,0:23:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望超声波图不仅是让堕胎派看到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We wanted the sonogram not just to be performed, for the sake of the abortionist,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.46,0:23:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,而且是为了让那个女人看到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but also to be displayed for the woman to see{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.77,0:24:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们的全部目标\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That was the whole goal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.40,0:24:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这有个模糊的东西\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This little blurry thing right here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.99,0:24:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,如果把注意力集中在这，你会看到一个点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you focus kind of right there and you see a little flicker{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.90,0:24:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,那是心跳，心脏活动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's the heartbeat. Cardiac activity{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.62,0:24:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,法律规定，医生必须向病人描述她在屏幕上看到的东西\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The law says a doctor has to describe what she sees on the screen to the patient,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.91,0:24:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,给她一个改变主意的机会\N{\fnarial\fs12\}giving her a chance to change her mind,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.01,0:24:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,看到她的错误，意识到她将要做什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to see the error of her ways and realize what she's about to do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.17,0:24:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这就目的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's the idea{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.88,0:24:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这是国家强加给妇女的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is the state imposing it upon the woman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.56,0:24:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,她已经请了一位医生和她讨论这个问题，并帮她解决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She has engaged a doctor to discuss this with her and help her come to a resolution{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.79,0:24:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,她没有参与德克萨斯州的立法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She did not engage the legislature of the state of Texas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.57,0:24:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}德克萨斯生命权组织坚信{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is the strong conviction of Texas Right to Life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.07,0:24:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}立法机构应该努力阻止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the legislature should work to stop abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.14,0:24:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在国会中，我们有能力引导对话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In the capitol, we have the capacity to direct the conversation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.37,0:24:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有的堕胎都是不公正的暴力行为，应该被拒绝{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}All elective abortion is a violent act of injustice and should be rejected{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.76,0:24:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你以共和党人的身份经营德克萨斯州…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you're running in Texas as a Republican{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.01,0:25:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对子宫里的人类婴儿的不人道行为…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}An inhumane action to a human child in the womb{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.82,0:25:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须同意亲生命的原则\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…you have to claim to agree with pro-life principles{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.89,0:25:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}希德•米勒协助通过了强有力的立法以保护未出生者{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Sid Miller helped pass powerful legislation to protect the unborn{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.53,0:25:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}谢谢你，上帝保佑{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Thank you and God bless{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.91,0:25:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以被选为农业专员\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You can be elected as agriculture commissioner{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.62,0:25:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以因为堕胎问题而当选本州首席财务官\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You can be elected as the chief financial officer of our state because of abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.23,0:25:21.34,自定义,,0,0,0,,唐纳·哈罗德   德州州代表
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.25,0:25:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是因为你在数字方面的技能\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not because of your skills with numbers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.84,0:25:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们必须通过一项最强有力的亲生命法案{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We must pass one of the strongest pieces of pro-life legislation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.61,0:25:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,而是因为你有能力通过立法来阻止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But because of your skill at getting legislation passed to obstruct access to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.88,0:25:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是这个问题在德州的强大地位\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's how powerful this issue is in Texas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.02,0:25:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是亲生命组织变得如此强大的原因\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's how powerful pro-life advocacy groups have become{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.10,0:25:43.56,自定义,,0,0,0,,里克•佩里   政府官员（共和党）
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.29,0:25:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我签署了一项超声波法律{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I signed a sonogram law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.87,0:25:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这样面对痛苦抉择的母亲们才能真正看到{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}so mothers facing that agonizing choice can actually see{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.84,0:25:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我知道{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I know it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.88,0:25:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它有用{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}works{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.93,0:25:53.07,自定义,,0,0,0,,国家生命权公约 2015年
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.74,0:26:00.03,自定义,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔•特拜斯   国家生命权协会主席
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.00,0:25:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望看到所有未出生的孩子受到保护，我们相信\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We want to see all unborn children protected, and we believe that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.32,0:26:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一直在做的仍然是最好的方法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}what we've been doing is still the best way to approach it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.41,0:26:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然而，有关堕胎的另一轮斗争正在…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Yet another round in the abortion battle has been fought on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.10,0:26:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们的障碍一直是最高法院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But our roadblock has always been the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.45,0:26:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法院拒绝推翻“罗诉韦德案”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Court declined to overrule Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.56,0:26:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将继续努力推翻它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're gonna keep plugging away to overturn Roe v. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.88,0:26:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们相信这个国家不应该杀死自己的孩子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because we believe this country shouldn't be killing its babies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.04,0:26:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是一个法律问题，一个宪法问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Is it a legal question, a constitutional question,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.61,0:26:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个医学问题，一个哲学问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a medical question, a philosophical question,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.90,0:26:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个宗教问题，亦或还是什么？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a religious question, or what is it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.05,0:26:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,全国各地还有其他病例\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There had been other cases around the country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.25,0:26:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,试图挑战当地的堕胎法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}trying to challenge local abortion laws{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.38,0:26:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们的案子是第一个到达美国最高法院的案件\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But our case was the first to get to the US Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.93,0:26:45.30,自定义,,0,0,0,,（重大犯罪）
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.97,0:26:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,德克萨斯州的法律规定，堕胎是非法的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The law in Texas was that abortion was illegal,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.85,0:26:50.06,自定义,,0,0,0,,（我想终止妊娠，因为经济困难）
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.09,0:26:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有一个不想要孩子的孕妇…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and we had a woman who was already pregnant who didn't want to be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.77,0:26:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,她不想公开她的名字\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and she didn't want her name public{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.77,0:26:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们想，那就用“约翰•杜/简•罗”（无名氏）\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, we thought, "Well, John Doe, Jane Roe"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.34,0:27:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,而亨利•韦德是达拉斯地区的检察官\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Henry Wade was the district attorney in Dallas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.35,0:27:08.01,自定义,,0,0,0,,萨拉·韦汀顿   律师
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.74,0:27:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,很明显，很多女性都受到了这个问题的影响\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it was clear that so many women were affected by this issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.38,0:27:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,每周四有一架飞机离开达拉斯去加利福尼亚\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There was a flight that left Dallas every Thursday going to California,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.90,0:27:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在那次航行中，通常会有10个或更多的女性去加州堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and there were usually ten or a few more women on that flight going out to California for abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.62,0:27:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,人们要去科罗拉多\N{\fnarial\fs12\}People were going to Colorado{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.45,0:27:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人都飞到纽约去了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And a lot of people were flying to New York{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.08,0:27:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,有成千上万的妇女曾经非法堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there were thousands of women who had had illegal abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.06,0:27:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,她们自己做了堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who had done their own abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.64,0:27:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们提出了一个集体诉讼\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so we filed a class action{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.64,0:27:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,说这是所有已怀孕或可能怀孕的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to say that this is a case for all women who are or might become pregnant{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,并希望选择堕胎的妇女的情况\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and want the option of abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.14,0:27:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我26岁\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I was 26{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.26,0:27:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我是最高法院有史以来最年轻的律师\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I was the youngest person ever to argue a case in the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.29,0:27:55.54,自定义,,0,0,0,,（金发律师在法庭上捍卫堕胎）
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.80,0:27:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们不是来提倡堕胎的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are not here to advocate abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.94,0:27:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们不要求法庭裁决堕胎是件好事{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We do not ask this court to rule that abortion is good,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.23,0:28:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或是在任何特定情况下都可取{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}or desirable in any particular situation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.95,0:28:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们来这里是为了倡导女性{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are here to advocate for the right of a woman to determine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.45,0:28:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是否有权决定，将继续或终止妊娠{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}whether or not she would continue or terminate a pregnancy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.40,0:28:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,9位中老年男人对“罗诉韦德案”进行了辩论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Roe against Wade was argued to nine middle-aged-to-elderly men{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.24,0:28:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个保守的法庭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a conservative Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.64,0:28:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,这个法庭有4人是由尼克松任命的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a Court with four Nixon appointees{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.92,0:28:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们的出现，将使最高法院比以往任何时候都要保守{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Their presence is expected to make the Court more conservative than at any time in recent memory{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.06,0:28:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但在那个时候，堕胎并不是一个党派的问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But abortion was not a partisan issue at that time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.97,0:28:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个医学问题，一个社会问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a medical problem, it was a social problem{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.28,0:28:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}基本的宪法问题是，未出生的胎儿是否是一个人，不是吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Basic constitutional question is whether or not an unborn fetus is a person, isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.60,0:28:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,有一次一位法官对我说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}At one point a justice had said to me,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.69,0:28:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“你认为人类的生命从何时开始？ ”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"When do you believe human life begins?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.08,0:28:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我说，好吧，法官大人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I said, "Well, Your Honor,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.81,0:28:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没必要去讨论那个精准时刻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we did not try to say exactly what moment that was,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.29,0:28:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这是没有答案的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There is no one answer to that"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.49,0:28:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的宗教对这个问题有不同的答案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Different religions have different answers to that question,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.81,0:29:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但是没有法律标准说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but there is no legal standard that said,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.59,0:29:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“这一刻，胎儿就变成了人”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"At this point the fetus becomes a human"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.01,0:29:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，问题是，谁来做这个决定？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, the question is, who gets to make the decision?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.97,0:29:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,是女人，还是政府？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Is it the woman, or is it the government?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.78,0:29:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我的立场一直是，它不是政府\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And my position has always been it's not the government{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.16,0:29:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}晚上好，在一个里程碑式的裁决中{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Good evening. In a landmark ruling,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.06,0:29:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最高法院今天将堕胎合法化{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the Supreme Court today legalized abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.29,0:29:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法院以7比2的比例{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Court split seven to two{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.69,0:29:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法官拜伦•怀特和威廉姆•伦奎斯特持反对意见{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}with Justices Byron White and William Rehnquist dissenting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.89,0:29:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个决定使堕胎在很大程度上成为私事{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The decision made abortion largely a private matter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.07,0:29:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并命令各州不得立法法律禁止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and ordered the states to make no laws forbidding it,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.85,0:29:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}除非是在（妊娠期）最后几个月{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}except possibly during the final months{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.44,0:29:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,当罗案曝光时，每个人都感到震惊\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When Roe went through, it was a shock to everyone{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.35,0:29:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,想要走到对立面去\N{\fnarial\fs12\}To go so far over to the other side,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.22,0:29:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,把一切都交到女人手里，实质上废除了法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to put everything in the woman's hand and essentially dismantle the laws{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.52,0:29:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,如今在其他任何州，你都不能通过法律反对堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Now, in any other state, you couldn't pass laws against abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.66,0:29:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,或者直接禁止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}not forbidding it directly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.89,0:29:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一项宪法权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a constitutional right{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.34,0:29:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,罗案最终判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Roe decision held{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.17,0:29:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,妇女有权在前两个孕程终止妊娠\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that women have the right to terminate a pregnancy in the first two trimesters,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.50,0:30:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,只有在怀孕晚期，州政府才有权禁止堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and then it's only at the third trimester that the state has the right to prohibit abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.81,0:30:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,除非是为了保护妇女的生命或健康\N{\fnarial\fs12\}except when necessary to preserve a woman's life or health{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.49,0:30:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,当“罗诉韦德案”的判决宣布时\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When the Roe v. Wade decision was handed down,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.74,0:30:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,计划生育协会一直致力于妇女的生殖健康和避孕措施\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood had been devoted to women's reproductive health and access to contraception{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.65,0:30:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,地方分会不得不自问\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the local chapters had to ask themselves,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.72,0:30:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“既然合法了，我们现在是否要提供堕胎？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"Are we gonna provide abortions now that they are legal?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.72,0:30:33.61,自定义,,0,0,0,,菲•沃莱顿   计划生育协会前主席
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这确实是一个反思的时刻，对组织来说非常艰难\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was really a moment of reflection that was very tough for the organization{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.98,0:30:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,当它第一次成为合法的时候\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When it first became legal,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.33,0:30:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,计生联合会并不热衷于堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood was not keen on abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.06,0:30:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,全国各地的分支机构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Various affiliates around the country,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.28,0:30:47.32,自定义,,0,0,0,,汤姆•戴维斯牧师    计生协会咨询处
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.60,0:30:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人都不想提供堕胎，他们真的不想\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a lot of them didn't want to do abortions. They really didn't{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.66,0:30:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,委员会分成了两派\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The board would be divided{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.99,0:30:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,一半的人愿意，另一半则不想\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Half the people would want to, the other half wouldn't{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.90,0:30:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}医生检查了你的身体，一切正常后{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Now, after the doctor's examined you and everything is all right,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.81,0:30:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他要做的第一件事是使用窥镜，这是…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the first thing he's going to do is use the speculum. This is the…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.65,0:31:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们接连转向支持的一边\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But one by one, they swung over to the active side{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.93,0:31:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们这么做的时候，那些不喜欢堕胎的人会从董事会辞职\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when they did, the people who didn't like abortion would resign from the board{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.72,0:31:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,其他人会加入进来，而且现在已经承诺\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and other people would come on, and it's committed now,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.49,0:31:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“罗诉韦德案”的判决已赋予了这项权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}committed to this right, given by the Roe v. Wade decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.41,0:31:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有任何法院的意见能够改变上帝的法律{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}No court opinion can change the law of God{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.08,0:31:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}必须探讨一切法律的可能性{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Every legal possibility must be explored{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.62,0:31:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以挑战美国最高法院的意见{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to challenge the opinion of the United States Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.54,0:31:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命始于受孕{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Life begins at conception{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.82,0:31:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}保护未出生的生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Protect the life of the unborn{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.30,0:31:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，只要没有纽约的法律，或者“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, as long as there was no New York law or no Roe v. Wade,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.69,0:31:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那么女人真的，你知道，就只是法外之徒\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the woman was really, you know, an outlaw{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.96,0:31:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,她四处奔走，试图走一些违法的途径\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She was moving around, trying to get some procedure that was against the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.23,0:31:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人真的想要阻止她\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And nobody really tried to stop her very much{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.24,0:31:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但是当法院说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But when the Court said,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.46,0:31:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“你有权做出这个决定，你有权利定义你的生活”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"You have the right to make this decision. You have the right to define your life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.12,0:31:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,不是宗教\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not religion"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.21,0:31:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不可接受的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That was unacceptable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.69,0:32:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}滚出去！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Get out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.65,0:32:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天这里不会有任何谋杀{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There won't be any murder here today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，基督教徒已经参与了各种反堕胎运动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, the Catholics were already involved with various pro-life things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.01,0:32:17.47,自定义,,0,0,0,,“拯救行动”训练片段
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.30,0:32:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但“拯救行动”确实源于福音派\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But for Operation Rescue, the genesis really was more evangelical{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.96,0:32:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们欢欣鼓舞，主啊，哈利路亚，荣耀归于上帝{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We rejoice, Lord. Hallelujah. Glory to God{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.14,0:32:28.46,自定义,,0,0,0,,托利•纽曼  “拯救行动”主席
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.61,0:32:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,这个名字来自箴言第24章第11节\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The name comes from Proverbs 24:11{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.62,0:32:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,圣经中说，“拯救那些被不公正地判处死刑的人”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Biblical verse that says, "Rescue those unjustly sentenced to die"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.87,0:32:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以把其他人锁到这条管子上{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Someone else can be hooked up to this pipe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.54,0:32:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天这里不允许堕胎，今天不能有堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There'll be no abortions in here today. No abortions in here today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.26,0:32:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们的座右铭是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so our motto was,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.40,0:32:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“我们是在拯救今天被判死刑的无辜儿童”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"We're here to rescue the innocent child sentenced to die today"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.99,0:32:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人们都到街上去，还有好几百人…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}People out into the street. There's hundreds more…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.46,0:32:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,这是要即刻行动的事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a very immediate thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.50,0:32:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎是军事援救行动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Almost militaristic. Operation Rescue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.57,0:32:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是来拯救这些婴儿的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're here to rescue these babies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.53,0:32:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法官，政客们{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The judges, the politicians,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.05,0:32:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们得到了信号，就像计生协会一样{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they're getting the signal, as is Planned Parenthood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.46,0:33:01.12,自定义,,0,0,0,,兰道尔•泰瑞  “拯救行动”发起人
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.85,0:33:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}合法杀害儿童的日子已经屈指可数了，我们会赢的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Legalized child killing's days are numbered… We will win{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.53,0:33:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一种现象\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is a phenomenon{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.80,0:33:08.06,自定义,,0,0,0,,威奇托（堪萨斯州）
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.95,0:33:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这真的是我们基督信仰的额外工作\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was really an outworking of our Christian faith{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.54,0:33:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，这是救援行动的中心\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, this is the epicenter of Operation Rescue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.05,0:33:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这曾经是一个堕胎诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is a former abortion clinic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.22,0:33:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我们实际上占领了这个地方，这是一个堕胎工厂\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We actually took this place that was an abortion mill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.10,0:33:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们关闭了它，并改造它，现在变成我们的总部\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We closed it down, we remodeled it, and now we've made it our headquarters{\r}
