Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.13,0:38:47.55,自定义,,0,0,0,,蒂勒医生诊所
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.85,0:38:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,与这家诊所和蒂勒医生的关系，对我来说真的很重要\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The tie that this clinic has to Dr. Tiller is really important to me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.90,0:38:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，即使面对我们的一个从业者被暗杀的情况\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, that even in the face of assassinating one of our providers,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.08,0:39:00.10,自定义,,0,0,0,,科莲•麦克尼可斯   妇科医生
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.09,0:39:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们仍然会提供治疗，因为妇女仍然值得这种治疗\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we were still gonna provide that care because women still deserve that care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.26,0:39:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会为你做检查，确保一切正常\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we do a checkup for you, make sure everything's okay{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.84,0:39:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Right{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.24,0:39:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有很多创伤记忆是关于堕胎运动中发生的事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There's a lot of traumatic memory of things that have happened in the abortion movement,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.11,0:39:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在被轰炸的诊所中，医疗服务提供者成为了目标\N{\fnarial\fs12\}of clinics being bombed, providers being targeted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.14,0:39:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你是个凶手，该让自己的灵魂下地狱{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You are a killer, condemning your own soul to hell{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.90,0:39:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，你的家庭有可能成为目标\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, the potential that your family will be targeted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.85,0:39:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}约翰逊大夫在我们的城市里杀害儿童{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Dr. Johnson has been killing children in our city{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.91,0:39:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人可能会出现在你家，或者你孩子的学校\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That people may show up at your home or at your kids' school{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.80,0:39:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,所有实际行医的困难，与对你和家人的安全威胁\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And you layer all of this difficulty of actually practicing medicine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.13,0:39:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,被联系在了一起\N{\fnarial\fs12\}with the threat to safety or harm to you or your family,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.29,0:39:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,对于很多人来说，这是个非常艰难的选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}it becomes a really difficult choice to make for many people{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.49,0:39:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“反选择”运动的策略之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And one of the strategies of the anti-choice movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.63,0:39:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是羞辱人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is to shame people{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.32,0:39:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们杀了你的孩子，他们不会让你…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They kill your baby. They won't let you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.56,0:39:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,对那些提供堕胎服务的人，和堕了胎的人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}People who provide abortions and people who have abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.36,0:40:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…你不能杀了你的孩子！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…You don't kill your baby!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.89,0:40:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想控制一个人生育的时间和数量\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you think about controlling when and if and how many children somebody has,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.92,0:40:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这是父权制的绝对体现\N{\fnarial\fs12\}it's sort of the absolute demonstration of patriarchy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.25,0:40:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,因为控制人们的生育能力，会影响到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Because controlling people's fertility can affect{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.10,0:40:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他们能得到什么样的教育，可以从事什么样的职业\N{\fnarial\fs12\}what education they can get and what career they can have{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.45,0:40:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,以及他们在人生中能走多远\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and sort of how far they can go in life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.72,0:40:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎链中的薄弱环节\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The weak link in the abortion chain{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.26,0:40:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是实施实际堕胎的人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is the person doing the actual abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.62,0:40:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,在美国，能实施堕胎手术的人越来越少\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there's fewer and fewer abortionists that are doing them here in the United States{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.25,0:40:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们退休了，或者改了行\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they're retiring and they're moving on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.80,0:40:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们针对职业堕胎者的手段非常有效\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so we've been very effective in targeting particular abortionists{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.33,0:40:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们一个堕胎医生也没有，这地方就得关闭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If they don't have an abortionist, the place closes down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.86,0:40:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,当堕胎诊所关闭的时候，婴儿就会得救\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when abortion clinics close, babies get saved{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.97,0:40:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经关闭了这些堕胎诊所，让它们停业\N{\fnarial\fs12\}These are abortion clinics we've closed down, put them out of business{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.98,0:41:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在圣地亚哥，海岸区，劳伦斯，堪萨斯州\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is in San Diego, Oceanside, Lawrence, Kansas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.59,0:41:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢把它看成是一堵墙\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I like to look at it as a trophy wall{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.94,0:41:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可能已经关闭了数百个堕胎诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We have probably closed down hundreds of abortion clinics,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.67,0:41:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我最引以为傲的一件事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it's the one thing I'm most proud of{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.95,0:41:23.00,自定义,,0,0,0,,只有一家堕胎诊所的州
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.45,0:41:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,现在，有七个州只有一家提供堕胎服务的机构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Right now, there are seven states that have only one abortion provider,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.17,0:41:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这些州在妇女医疗保健方面受到限制\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and those states have been under siege in terms of restrictions on women's health care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.76,0:41:36.72,自定义,,0,0,0,,布里吉特·阿米莉   美国公民自由协会
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.23,0:41:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，我们一直在监控\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, we are constantly monitoring the patterns in the states{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.72,0:41:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,各州限制妇女堕胎的立法模式\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in terms of legislation that restricts women's access to abortion…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.99,0:41:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们已经看到许多州采取措施，取消对堕胎服务提供者的资助{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We've seen a lot of state moves to defund abortion providers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.25,0:41:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,想想我们需要做些什么，以阻止立法通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…thinking about what we need to do to block legislation from passing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.12,0:41:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们得到了法律的初步支持{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We got that law preliminarily enjoined{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.45,0:41:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,如果法案通过，我们会考虑向法院提出异议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then if it does pass, we consider bringing a court challenge{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.25,0:41:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，对于肯塔基的陷阱\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, for Kentucky TRAP{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.47,0:42:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,肯塔基州是一个很好的例子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Kentucky is a perfect example{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.38,0:42:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将尽我们所能做到最好\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are going to do the best that we can{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.00,0:42:05.54,自定义,,0,0,0,,马特•贝文   政府官员（共和党）
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.30,0:42:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,迎接肯塔基州新的一天\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to usher in a new day for Kentucky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.72,0:42:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在贝文州长上任之前\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Before Governor Bevin took office,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.57,0:42:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,肯塔基州有三家堕胎机构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}there were three abortion providers in Kentucky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.80,0:42:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}毫无疑问我绝对是亲生命派的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm unapologetically pro-life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.13,0:42:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他立即采取行动，逐一取缔堕胎诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And he sprung right into action to pick off abortion clinics one by one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.96,0:42:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}州长马特•贝文已经下令{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Governor Matt Bevin has ordered a Louisville{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.13,0:42:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}让路易斯维尔计划生育诊所立即停止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood clinic to stop performing abortions immediately{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.78,0:42:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是贝文政府第二次就堕胎问题起诉一家诊所{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For the second time, Bevin administration has sued a clinic over abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.19,0:42:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们立即终止了他们的工作{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we gave them an immediate cease and desiSt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.01,0:42:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们说过，如有必要，我们会发出禁制令{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We said that we would seek an injunction if necessary{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.72,0:42:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}共和党现在已经控制了国会和参议院{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Republicans now have control of both the House, the Senate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.12,0:42:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们原有三家堕胎诊所，现在只剩一家{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We had three abortion clinics. We are now down to one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.70,0:42:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,现在贝文州长正试图关闭最后一家诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And now Governor Bevin is trying to shut down the last remaining clinic,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.53,0:42:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,EMW妇女中心\N{\fnarial\fs12\}EMW Women's Center{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.65,0:42:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}贝文政府对堕胎诊所的新规定{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…Bevin administration's new rules for abortion clinics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.15,0:42:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在美国公民自由联盟，我们认为贝文州长正在做的事是违宪的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And at the ACLU, we think what Governor Bevin is doing is blatantly unconstitutional{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.88,0:43:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果法官站在马特•贝文州长一边{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If a judge sides with Governor Matt Bevin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.88,0:43:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}肯塔基将成为全国唯一没有堕胎诊所的州{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Kentucky will become the only state in the nation without an abortion clinic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.53,0:43:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,肯塔基州的情况是前所未有的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The situation in Kentucky really is unprecedented{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.85,0:43:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从来没见过这样的情况\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We have never seen a situation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.30,0:43:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们处在一个没有堕胎机构的州的边缘\N{\fnarial\fs12\}where we have been on the cusp of a state that has no abortion provider{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.30,0:43:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这对女性来说是非常可怕的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's incredibly dire for women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.97,0:43:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}关闭这个地方！贝文州长，把这个地方关了{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Close this place down! Governor Bevin, close this place down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.98,0:43:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在肯塔基州最后一家堕胎诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's exciting to see pro-life activity{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.68,0:43:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,看到亲生命运动是令人兴奋的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}at the last abortion clinic in Kentucky,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.53,0:43:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我一直期待着我们成为无堕胎州的那一刻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because I have been looking so forward to the moment when we have an abortion-free state{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.44,0:43:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们看看能不能把堕胎诊所的棺材钉上最后一颗钉子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And let's see if we can't put the final nail in the coffin of the abortion clinic there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.04,0:43:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们肯塔基州尊重人类生命的神圣性…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We in the Commonwealth of Kentucky respect the sanctity of human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.73,0:43:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,贝文州长的表现非常出色\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Governor Bevin's been fantastic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.99,0:43:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党人反对堕胎，支持十诫\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Republicans stand against abortion, stand for the Ten Commandments,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.64,0:43:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他们代表着男人和女人的婚姻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and they stand for marriage between a man and a woman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.22,0:43:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而共和党已经成为了道德的政党\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the Republican Party has kind of become the party of morality{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.39,0:44:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一场关乎美国灵魂和心灵的战争\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there's a war for the heart and soul of America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.33,0:44:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这场辩论是关于那些没有被征得同意的婴儿{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This debate is about little babies who haven't given their consent,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.42,0:44:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在是我们说适可而止的时候了{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it's about time we said enough is enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.97,0:44:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有人说国际计划生育协会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Nobody's saying that Planned Parenthood can't be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.71,0:44:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不能成为美国自愿堕胎的主要倡导者{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the leading advocate of abortion-on-demand in America,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.37,0:44:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我为什么要为此付钱呢？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but why do I have to pay for it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.32,0:44:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}华盛顿需要停止给他们拨款，向他们发出明确的信息{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Washington needs to defund them, send a clear message{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.21,0:44:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我今天来这里，是想要求我的参议员们{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I come here today to ask my fellow senators{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.01,0:44:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}投票撤销计划生育的资金{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to vote to defund Planned Parenthood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.57,0:44:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这种关于取消计划生育拨款的言论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Because this language and messaging around defunding Planned Parenthood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.61,0:44:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,已经非常普遍\N{\fnarial\fs12\}has been so pervasive,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.15,0:44:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我想普通民众相信\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think the general population believes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.05,0:44:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,取消对计划生育的资金意味着\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that defunding Planned Parenthood means{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.10,0:44:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,不为堕胎买单\N{\fnarial\fs12\}not paying for abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.98,0:44:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实上，根据法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But in fact, and by law,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.57,0:44:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,联邦政府并没有用于支付堕胎的资金\N{\fnarial\fs12\}no federal dollars go to pay for abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.07,0:44:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,每年有250万患者依赖计划生育\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Two and a half million patients depend on Planned Parenthood every single year{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.02,0:44:54.65,自定义,,0,0,0,,塞西尔•理查德斯   计划生育协会主席
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.45,0:44:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,为了避孕，为了检测和治疗性传播疾病…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}for birth control, for testing and treatment for sexually transmitted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.82,0:44:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不希望我们的税金流向那个组织\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We don't want our tax dollars going to that organization{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.37,0:45:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,用于他们提供的任何服务\N{\fnarial\fs12\}for any service that they provide{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.49,0:45:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,计划生育协会是一个大型的堕胎服务机构\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood is a mega abortion provider{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.52,0:45:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,全国大约三分之一的堕胎是由这个组织完成的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's about a third of all abortions performed in this country are done by that one organization{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.19,0:45:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只是把他们看成…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We just see them as{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.47,0:45:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,婴儿杀手\N{\fnarial\fs12\}um, as baby killers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.12,0:45:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}请和我一起欢迎美国总统{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Please join me in welcoming the President of the United States,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.34,0:45:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}巴拉克•奥巴马{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Barack Obama{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.08,0:45:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,说到堕胎问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when it comes to abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.30,0:45:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,它们很大程度上占据了民主党的议程\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they pretty much get to control the agenda in the Democratic Party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.69,0:45:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}计划生育协会不会扩展到任何地方{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood is not going anywhere{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.78,0:45:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天不会，明天也不会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's not going anywhere today, it's not going anywhere tomorrow{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.31,0:45:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这是众所周知的事实\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it's a known fact{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.24,0:45:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党人将通过反堕胎法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Republicans will pass pro-life legislation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.61,0:45:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们投票撤销对计划生育的拨款{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We voted to defund Planned Parenthood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.13,0:45:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}共和党人取得了巨大的进展，不仅是在国会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Republicans made huge gains, not only in the House,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.78,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有州长竞选和州立法的活动中…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but in governors' races and state legislative campaigns{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.17,0:45:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,现在的州议员中我们的共和党人占多数\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We now have Republican. majorities in state legislators{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.10,0:45:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信有33位共和党州长\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I believe 33 Republican Governors{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.69,0:45:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,多年来我们一直有一个计划，我们一直遵循它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We've had a game plan for many years, we're following it,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.00,0:46:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为它将会结出硕果\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I think it's coming to fruition{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.78,0:46:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对我们来说，为反堕胎事业挺身而出有何重要性？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What's so important for us to stand up for the cause of pro-life?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.13,0:46:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我取消了他们的假期，把他们带回来参加一个支持生命的特别会议{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I cancelled their vacations and I brought them back for a pro-life special session{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.44,0:46:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我相信我们会完成这项工作{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I'm convinced that we're going to get the job done{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.89,0:46:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,主要党派是共和党人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The general assembly is heavily Republican{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.35,0:46:19.00,自定义,,0,0,0,,密苏里州
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.09,0:46:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在两院都占有三分之二的席位\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They have a two-thirds majority in both Chambers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.58,0:46:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我在中西部的几个诊所提供堕胎服务\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I provide abortion care in several clinics in the MidweSt.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.12,0:46:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,诊所必须遵守层层加诸的规章制度\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and the clinics have to be able to comply with the layers and layers and layers of regulations that have been put on them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.82,0:46:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}国会正在通过一项立法{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Legislation is on its way to the House{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.79,0:46:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要求对堕胎诊所进行检查{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that would require inspections of abortion clinics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.54,0:46:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并对堕胎手术进行其他新的限制{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and enact other new restrictions on the procedure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.99,0:46:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们面临着更多的立法，更多的规章制度\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And now we're facing more legislation, more regulations,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.49,0:46:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,新的法案正在出台，新的法律正在生效，以及…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}new bills being introduced, new laws going into effect, and{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.88,0:46:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,日拱一卒的基础上，我们又能做多少呢\N{\fnarial\fs12\}on an almost day-to-day basis, what we can do might change{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.39,0:46:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}密苏里州的立法者制定了全国最长的堕胎等待期{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Missouri lawmakers have enacted one of the nation's longest abortion waiting periods{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.14,0:46:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}格里茨州长召集了一次特别会议{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Governor Greitens calls a special session{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.28,0:47:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}州议员又回来了——{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}State lawmakers are back--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.23,0:47:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在这些法案和听证会中，有太多失真的事实\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there's so much factual inaccuracy in these bills and in hearings,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.49,0:47:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得有人真的需要发出自己的声音\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I felt that somebody really needs to be a voice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.88,0:47:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,一个医学的声音，和一个科学的声音\N{\fnarial\fs12\}A voice for medicine and a voice for science{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.01,0:47:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，下午好\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Okay. Good afternoon{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.59,0:47:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我是妇产科医生科琳•麦克尼古拉斯，在圣路易斯执业\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm Dr. Colleen McNicholas. I'm an OB-GYN. I practice in St. Louis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.17,0:47:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不应该有“亲生命”或“亲选择”的法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There shouldn't be a pro-life or pro-choice law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.15,0:47:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,医疗保健政策中应该有一项重要的、以科学为基础的法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There should be a law in healthcare policy that is important and science-based{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.09,0:47:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但每一次我作证…\N- 为什么你的观念\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- But every single time I've testified… - Why is your opinion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.66,0:47:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,和其他人如此不同？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}so much different than theirs?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.53,0:47:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,来自反堕胎组织的说客也将出庭作证\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…lobbyists from the anti-choice group will also testify{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.44,0:47:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是一些书面证词…\N- 他们可以随便怎么说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- Here's some written testimony… - And they can say whatever they want{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.95,0:47:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,保护密苏里州妇女健康和安全的案例一个接一个\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…case by case, to protect the health and safety of women in Missouri{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.14,0:47:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,是李“医生”吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Is it Dr. Lee?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.52,0:47:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,不，参议员\N{\fnarial\fs12\}No, Senator{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.48,0:47:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，你不是医师，那是病理学家吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, you're not a physician. Are you a pathologist?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.71,0:47:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,完全不是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not at all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.73,0:47:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这让人很恼火\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Which is infuriating{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.25,0:47:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是在某些角度上，像是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Especially from sort of the standpoint of like{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.84,0:47:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,科学和证据，或者仅仅是事实\N{\fnarial\fs12\}science and evidence and…just facts{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.05,0:48:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,圣路易斯的堕胎诊所在提交\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The abortion clinic in St. Louis has not been complying with the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.58,0:48:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,并发症报告方面一直没有遵守法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in terms of turning over complication reports{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.19,0:48:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,每年我们都会推出几十个反堕胎的法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Every year we have dozens of pro-life bills introduced{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.68,0:48:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,议员们来找我说：“萨姆，我能做什么？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Lawmakers who come to me and say, "Sam, what can I do?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.18,0:48:17.89,自定义,,0,0,0,,萨姆•李  密苏里州生命权立法竞选
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.51,0:48:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以提出什么样的法案来减少堕胎？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"What type of bill can I introduce to reduce abortions?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.14,0:48:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一场猫鼠游戏，一方亲生命，另一方亲选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's a bit of a cat and mouse game between the pro-life pro-choice side,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.95,0:48:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,……没有在并发症报告中出现\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…is not turning in complication reports{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.10,0:48:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一项有关堕胎条例的法案再次在立法机关通过{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Once again a bill on abortion regulations moved through the legislature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.97,0:48:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他们必须有一个并发症的计划\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They have to have a complication plan{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.14,0:48:34.40,自定义,,0,0,0,,贾米拉•纳什   州议员
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.14,0:48:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我的感觉\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is how I feel{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.60,0:48:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不是在医学领域，好吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Okay? We're not in the field of medicine here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.09,0:48:40.21,自定义,,0,0,0,,安德鲁•科尼阁    州议员
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.78,0:48:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,政府是什么时候开始批准并发症计划的？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When did the government start approving complication plans?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.45,0:48:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为医生们会这样做\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I thought the doctors or the physicians would do that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.58,0:48:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的抱怨是，这应该适用于所有诊所\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Our complaint is that that should be for all clinics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.40,0:48:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果堕胎设施必须遵守某些规定，那么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If abortion facilities have to comply with certain things, then{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.82,0:48:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,其他提供类似护理水平的诊所也应当如此\N{\fnarial\fs12\}so too should other clinics that are providing similar levels of care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.69,0:48:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你还在为其他事情制定计划吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Are you putting plans together for anything else?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.73,0:48:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，你可以吃很多的猪肉！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I mean, you could eat too much pork!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.53,0:49:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,然而得了胆结石，你就得做手术\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And have a gallstone and you'd have to go through surgery{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.05,0:49:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我们只是在个人想要堕胎的时候才这么做呢？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Why is it that we're just doing this when it comes to individuals wanting to have an abortion?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.68,0:49:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我的意思是…\N- 这听起来很荒谬\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- Well, I mean it is… - It sounds so ridiculous{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.92,0:49:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎和其他任何医疗程序都不一样\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Abortion is different than just any other medical procedure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.65,0:49:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道民主党人和计生组织想要这样对待它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I know that the Democrats and Planned Parenthood want to treat it that way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.86,0:49:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道他们想以这种方式谈论它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I know they want to talk about in that way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.31,0:49:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但是去街上问问普通人的话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But talk to your average person on the street{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.66,0:49:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会告诉你，堕胎与结肠镜检查或拔牙是不同的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they're going to tell you that abortion is not the same as having a colonoscopy or having your tooth pulled{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.77,0:49:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,它是独一无二的，与众不同的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's something unique and different{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.73,0:49:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,没有其他的医疗程序\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There is no other medical procedure, none,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.93,0:49:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,没一个是像堕胎这样被立法的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}not one, that is legislated in the way that abortion is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.32,0:49:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,适可而止吧\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Enough is enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.93,0:49:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经准备好战斗到底，因为我厌倦了共和党\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm ready to go down fighting, because I'm tired of the Republican Party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.50,0:49:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在女性选择权的问题上欺凌她们\N{\fnarial\fs12\}bullying women when it comes to their right to choose{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.91,0:49:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'll tell you what{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.59,0:49:53.72,自定义,,0,0,0,,埃里克•格雷顿斯   政府官员（共和党）
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.51,0:49:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我很自豪能和这么多密苏里州的生命派在一起\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I am proud to be with so many people standing for life here in Missouri{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.72,0:50:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，从今天的角度来看\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, from the perspective of today,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.59,0:50:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为重要的是要记住\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think it's important to remember that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.98,0:50:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎并不是一直有党派之分\N{\fnarial\fs12\}abortion was not always so partisan{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.29,0:50:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党人也并非一直需要成为“亲生命派”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it wasn't always a requirement for the Republicans to be pro-life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.20,0:50:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上，这需要由非常聪明的…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In fact, it took years of cultivation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.60,0:50:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们担心有一百万个婴儿正在死去……{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're concerned that a million babies are dying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.33,0:50:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,…共和党战略家们多年来的培养\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…by very smart Republican strategists{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.33,0:50:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我们花了很多年才实现了这种政党的重新洗牌\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It took years to bring about that kind of party realignment,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.47,0:50:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,把堕胎作为一个社会文化问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the placing of abortion front-and-center as{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.97,0:50:39.97,自定义,,0,0,0,,杰瑞•法维尔    道德多数派\N（美国发起的主张奉行严格的基督教教义，反对政治变革的运动）
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.53,0:50:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,摆在我们政治的中心\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a social, cultural issue in our politics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.20,0:50:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们关心的是道德问题，家庭的破裂{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're concerned about the moral problems, the breakdown of the family{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.26,0:50:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们是为了美国儿童谋福祉而来{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We've come to seek the welfare of America's children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.40,0:50:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}愿上帝保佑你们，祝你们有美好的一天{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}God bless you and have a great day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.48,0:50:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这是在20世纪80年代\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it was accomplished in the 1980s,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.59,0:50:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,由社会、宗教和政治保守派组成的联盟完成的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}by this coalition of social and religious and political conservatives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.50,0:51:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这是随着罗纳德•里根的崛起而实现的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it was done with the rise of Ronald Reagan{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.13,0:51:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在1980年的选举中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The 1980 election is when abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.12,0:51:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎成了一个政治问题，和典型的共和党要事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}really becomes a political issue and particularly a Republican issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.39,0:51:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有三重主要责任\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We have a threefold primary responsibility{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.74,0:51:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}第一，让人们得到救赎，第二，让他们受洗{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Number one, get people saved. Number two, get them baptized{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.36,0:51:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}第三，让他们投票{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Number three, get them registered to vote{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.41,0:51:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,杰瑞•法维尔将福音派基督徒视为一场政治运动的基础\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Jerry Falwell saw evangelical Christians as the basis for a political movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.17,0:51:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,法维尔想要组织福音派选民\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Falwell wanted to organize evangelical voters,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.33,0:51:31.32,自定义,,0,0,0,,兰道尔•巴莫   宗教史学家
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.68,0:51:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在此之前，他们在政治上在政治上不活跃\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who up until that time had not been politically active{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.48,0:51:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在我看来，我们在十诫方面一点长进都没有{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's always seemed to me we haven't improved by one iota on the Ten Commandments{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.53,0:51:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,法维尔和宗教右翼认为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Falwell and the religious right identifies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.90,0:51:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,罗纳德•里根作为一名候选人，将推动他们的议程\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Ronald Reagan as a candidate who would push their agenda,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.06,0:51:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的社会保守议程\N{\fnarial\fs12\}their socially conservative agenda{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.52,0:51:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宗教美国正在觉醒{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Religious America is awakening,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.15,0:51:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也许是时候了，为了我们的国家{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}perhaps just in time, for our country's sake{\r}
