Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.42,0:52:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们不会直接说出来\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but we are not going to come right out and say it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.98,0:52:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}即将到来的选举对我们来说，是一个巨大的考验{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This coming election's gonna be a big test for us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.00,0:52:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这次选举是为了让美国再次伟大{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This election is to make America great again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.96,0:53:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1}我告诉过共和党人{\b0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I have told the Republicans{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.37,0:53:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你要忠于自己深信的一套道德戒律{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that you are loyal to a certain set of moral precepts in which you deeply believe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.00,0:53:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,威里克认识到福音派选民的选举潜力\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Weyrich recognized the electoral potential of evangelical voters,{\r}
