Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.16,0:53:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我当然反对堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Well, I am certainly opposed to abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.09,0:53:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为我认为这是在杀死一个未出生的孩子{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because I think it's killing an unborn child{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.14,0:53:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,随着总统选举开始成形……\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And as the presidential election begins to take shape{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.01,0:53:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}关键问题是什么？在我们的判断中{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What are the key issues? In our judgment,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.54,0:53:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命的权利，保护未出生的人{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the right to life, protect the unborn{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.61,0:54:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些是关键问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}These are key issues{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.85,0:54:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,威里克说，实际上“我们发现了自身的问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Weyrich says, in effect, "We found our issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.79,0:54:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎会是一个为我们所用政治问题”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Abortion is going to work for us as a political issue"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.80,0:54:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}数百万未出生的毫无抵抗力的婴儿……{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Millions of unborn defenseless babies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.62,0:54:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,当你试图改变国家政治制度的动态时\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When you are trying to change the dynamic of the political system in the country,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.44,0:54:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须通过情绪化的路线来解决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you have to do it through emotional issues{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.07,0:54:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在我们华盛顿的演播室的是杰里•法维尔{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In our Washington studios is Jerry Falwell{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.85,0:54:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}美国自1973年以来就违反了生命的尊严原则{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}America has violated the principle of the dignity of life since 1973{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.76,0:54:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们强烈支持生命，我们的第一要务——{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we're very strongly pro-life. Our first order of business--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.68,0:54:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,还有什么比母亲和婴儿更加感性化呢？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And what is more emotional than motherhood and babies?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.70,0:54:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,从那时起，里根的竞选团队开始将堕胎视为一个政治问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}At that point the Reagan campaign begins to embrace abortion as a political issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.94,0:54:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我相信……{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.91,0:54:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你终止怀孕的时候，你是在夺走一个人的生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that when you interrupt the pregnancy, you are taking a human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.77,0:54:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在1980年的选举中获胜\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Which they ride through the 1980 election{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.91,0:54:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有趣的是，一位全国领先的民意调查专家说{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's interesting. One of the nation's leading pollsters says{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.14,0:55:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}里根赢得了白人选民的选票{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Reagan is winning the votes of the white electors,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.57,0:55:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们是福音派传教士的追随者，所谓的“道德多数派”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who are followers of the evangelical preachers,the so-called Moral Majority,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.15,0:55:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们在选举中一直很活跃{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who have been active in the election{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.97,0:55:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个团体为里根在选举中提供了明确的优势{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This group is providing Reagan with his clear margin in the election{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.28,0:55:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}罗纳德•里根获得压倒性的胜利…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\} Ronald Reagan's overwhelming victory{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.16,0:55:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}里根赢得了44个州，获得479张选票{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Reagan won 44 states, with 479 electoral votes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.98,0:55:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他们着手改变共和党内部的动态\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They set out to change the dynamic in the Republican party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.14,0:55:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他们提名了一个有用的人，他们成功了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So they nominated somebody that would be useful. And they succeeded{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.46,0:55:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是“罗诉韦德案”的8年之后\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was now eight years after Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.35,0:55:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,结束堕胎的未来，似乎将属于共和党\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it seemed like the future of ending abortion was going to be in the Republican party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.00,0:55:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,里根确实给了亲生命派团体很多希望\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Reagan really gave a lot of hope to the pro-life community{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.65,0:55:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,身为基督徒，会支持联邦政府为堕胎拨款吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Can a person be a Christian and support federal funding of abortion?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.83,0:55:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我相信，堕胎是在夺走人的生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe in an abortion you are taking a human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.56,0:56:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你相信这一点，那肯定是有宗教内涵的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you believe that, it very definitely has a religious connotation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.96,0:56:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他只是重申了他对\N{\fnarial\fs12\}He just reaffirmed his support of{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.29,0:56:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,亲生命运动所代表的一切的支持\N{\fnarial\fs12\}everything the pro-life movement represents{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.92,0:56:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问他和我们站在一起\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There's never been any question that he was with us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.21,0:56:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们热爱生命！我们想要生命！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We love life! We want life!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.42,0:56:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在反堕胎团体的思想中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In the mind of the pro-life community,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.84,0:56:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎权在法律上是不正常的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the right to abortion was an aberration in the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.80,0:56:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，随着里根总统的当选\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, with the election of President Reagan,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.54,0:56:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们认为，下一步将是尝试推翻“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we thought the next step would be to try to reverse Roe versus Wade{\r}
