Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.23,0:56:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最高法院废除了公立学校的祷告和十诫{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is the Supreme Court that has abolished prayer and the Ten Commandments from the public schools{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.62,0:56:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是最高法院的判决{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is Supreme Court decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.88,0:56:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}迫使我们带上孩子乘坐公交车{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that have brought upon us forced busing and put our children on buses{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.87,0:56:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}穿过城市把他们送去父母不想让他们去的学校{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and send them across town to some school that their parents don't want them to go to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.81,0:56:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是最高法院的判决{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is Supreme Court decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.03,0:56:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}导致了色情作品泛滥{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that have unleashed the pornography{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.33,0:57:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}充斥我们的报摊和电视{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that has invaded our newsstands and our television{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.71,0:57:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是最高法院的判决{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is Supreme Court decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.89,0:57:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}废除了死刑和对犯罪的威慑{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that have abolished capital punishment and deterrents against crime{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.07,0:57:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当然，还是最高法院的判决{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And, of course, it is the Supreme Court decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.64,0:57:16.02,自定义,,0,0,0,,菲利斯·施拉夫利    政治策划
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.45,0:57:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}导致了我们这个时代的残忍悲剧{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that has brought about this tragic evil of our time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.60,0:57:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最高法院在1973年做出的一项裁决{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}A Supreme Court decision, in 1973,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.01,0:57:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发明了一项新的权利，妇女可以杀死自己未出生的孩子{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that invented this new right of a woman to kill her unborn baby{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.21,0:57:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,如果堕胎是一项宪法权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If abortion is a constitutional right,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.50,0:57:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,最重要的是要推翻“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the most important thing was to overturn Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.61,0:57:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,为了做到这一点，你必须改变法庭上的法官\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In order to do that, you had to change the justices on the Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.86,0:57:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,没有别的办法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There's no other way{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.82,0:57:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你需要尽可能快地重组最高法院{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You need, as quickly as possible, a reconstituting of the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.13,0:57:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不认为现任的法官会改变观念\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We just didn't think that the current justices would have changed their minds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.29,0:57:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我将向参议院提名{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I will send to the Senate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.03,0:57:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亚利桑那州的桑德拉•戴•奥康纳{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the nomination of Judge Sandra Day O'Connor, of Arizona{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.70,0:57:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最高法院的第一位女性{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The first woman on the Supreme Court,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.66,0:57:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}桑德拉•戴•奥康纳法官{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Judge Sandra Day O'Connor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.38,0:57:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她今天告诉参议院，她坚决反对堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She told the Senate today that she is firmly opposed to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.11,0:58:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在堕胎方面，我反对将其视为节育问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In the area of abortion is that I am opposed to it as a matter of birth control{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.98,0:58:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，里根总统任命了奥康纳\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, President Reagan appointed O'Connor,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.49,0:58:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,然后任命了大法官斯卡利亚和肯尼迪大法官\N{\fnarial\fs12\}then appointed Justice Scalia and Justice Kennedy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.52,0:58:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在亲生命派团体中，“罗诉韦德案”有希望被推翻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And in the pro-life community there was the hope that Roe versus Wade may get overturned{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.04,0:58:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们认为最高法院正朝着这个方向迈进\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we thought the Court was moving much closer in that direction{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.84,0:58:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你是否有这种感觉\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Are you getting the feeling that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.55,0:58:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,某种运动正在进行，最终会侵蚀“罗诉韦德案”？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}some sort of movement is under way that would ultimately erode Roe v. Wade?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.48,0:58:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅是有感觉，我也参与其中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm not only getting a feeling. I'm part of it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.13,0:58:33.59,自定义,,0,0,0,,丹尼斯•荷安    美国生命联合会
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.56,0:58:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 它发生了？\N- 它正在发生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- It's happened?   - It's happening{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.36,0:58:41.83,自定义,,0,0,0,,（堕胎诊所的执照研讨）
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.19,0:58:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,美国生命联合会是其中主要参与者之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Americans United for Life is one of the main players in this{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.32,0:58:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的策略是一次只提出一项反堕胎的限制\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They have a strategy of one anti-abortion restriction at a time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.18,0:58:47.40,自定义,,0,0,0,,（州立法机关变成新的战场）
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.89,0:58:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这个策略可以通过州立法机关，也可能上到最高法院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}which could pass state legislatures and maybe get up to the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.55,0:58:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,并推翻罗案的判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and overturn Roe against Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.71,0:58:53.00,自定义,,0,0,0,,（最高法院听证堕胎辩论）
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.52,0:58:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,1989年的一起堕胎案件中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it looked like it actually might happen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.52,0:58:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这种情况似乎真的会发生\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in an abortion case in 1989{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.56,0:59:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但奥康纳法官对“罗诉韦德案”的支持，让世界感到意外\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But Justice O'Connor surprised the world by sustaining Roe against Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.85,0:59:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这让最高法院的保守派极为沮丧\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that was a matter of extreme frustration to the Court's conservatives{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.96,0:59:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为奥康纳法官不想成为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think Justice O'Connor didn't want to be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.31,0:59:14.46,自定义,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳•科尔伯特    生育权律师
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.17,0:59:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,法庭上第一位，也是唯一一位剥夺宪法权利的女性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the first and lone woman on the Court taking away a settled constitutional right{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.83,0:59:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,所以她支持“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so she upheld Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.49,0:59:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但是布莱克门法官做了个非常非常重要的声明\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But Justice Blackmun made a very, very important statement,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.90,0:59:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他在法官席上读到说，“罗诉韦德案”正岌岌可危\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and he read it from the bench and he said, "Roe versus Wade is hanging by a thread{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.34,0:59:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们处在一个非常脆弱的环境中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are in a very tenuous circumstance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.76,0:59:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只差一票之遥，下一个案子就可以了”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're only one vote away. The next case could do it"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.22,0:59:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之后，政治形势真的发生了变化\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And after that, the political situation really changed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.88,0:59:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像广阔而平静的天空中的一千个光点{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Like a thousand points of light in a broad and peaceful sky{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.57,0:59:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,当老布什成为总统的时候\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When H.W. became president,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.25,0:59:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们以为他会是一个亲选择派的总统\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we thought that he would be a pro-choice president{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.26,0:59:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}堕胎分歧，在我们党内，我们为那些持一种观点的人留出了空间{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Abortion divides. We have room in our party for people that feel one way,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.34,0:59:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有亲生命派的，也有亲选择派的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}pro-life, or pro-choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.08,0:59:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是存在分歧的问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is an issue that divides{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.72,1:00:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,当他是国会议员时\N{\fnarial\fs12\}When he was a congressman,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.74,1:00:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他一直被认为是计划生育的大力支持者\N{\fnarial\fs12\}he had been known as a big supporter of family planning,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.41,1:00:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,以至于他的一些同事称他为“安全套”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to the point that some of his colleagues called him "Rubbers"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.55,1:00:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你赞成反堕胎的宪法修正案吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Do you favor a constitutional amendment against abortion?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.37,1:00:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我反对这样的修正案{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I oppose such an amendment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.14,1:00:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}第35届共和党全国代表大会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The 35th Republican National Convention{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.84,1:00:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}本周最大的挑战是什么？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What's the big challenge here this week?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.88,1:00:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我真的不知道，主要是…堕胎吧{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I really don't know. I-- Abortion, mostly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.57,1:00:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人们真的需要明白{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}People really need to understand that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.74,1:00:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲生命派现在是支撑乔治•布什的中坚力量{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the pro-lifers are now the backbone that is holding up George Bush{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.21,1:00:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}乔治•布什必须采取强有力的亲家庭立场{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}George Bush has to take a strong pro-family position{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.84,1:00:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}坦率地说，这意味着在堕胎问题上立场坚定{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And frankly, that means a strong position on abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.31,1:00:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,布什转头反对亲选择派\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Bush turned against choice,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.77,1:00:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他的立场要比…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and he took on a position that was stronger than{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.73,1:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,比里根的以往任何时候都要强硬\N{\fnarial\fs12\}than anything Reagan ever did{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.14,1:00:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为堕胎是错误的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe that abortion is wrong{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.96,1:00:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为我们应该努力推翻“罗诉韦德案”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe that we should work to overturn Roe vs. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.26,1:01:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为，各州应该有权禁止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I believe that states should have the right to prohibit abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.61,1:01:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不做很多保证，但我会给你做一个{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I don't make many guarantees, but I'll make you one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.98,1:01:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宾夕法尼亚州将是联邦第一个{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Pennsylvania will be the first state in the Union{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.89,1:01:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}彻底结束这一噩梦的州，并禁止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to end the nightmare once and for all and to outlaw abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.89,1:01:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最高法院第91-744号案件{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Supreme Court case number 91-744{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.78,1:01:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宾夕法尼亚州东南计划生育协会诉凯西案{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood of Southeast Pennsylvania versus Casey{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.95,1:01:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,计划生育协会诉凯西案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood versus Casey{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.33,1:01:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,于1992年上诉到最高法院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That went up to the Supreme Court in 1992{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.34,1:01:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是美国最严格的堕胎法之一{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…one of the most restrictive abortion laws in the nation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.61,1:01:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,很多亲生命派人士认为这将会推翻“罗诉韦德案”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And a lot of pro-life people thought this was going to be the case that would overturn Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.31,1:01:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布什政府要求最高法院{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Bush administration asked the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.01,1:01:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}支持进一步限制妇女堕胎的权利{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to support further limitations on a woman's right to have an abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.05,1:01:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布什总统尽其所能{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}President Bush has done all he can do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.38,1:01:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以确保我的论点可能会被置若罔闻{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to ensure that my arguments are likely to fall on deaf ears{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.34,1:01:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全相信我们会输\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I was totally convinced that we were going to lose{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.30,1:01:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为他在法庭上塞满了{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For he has packed the Court with justices{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.89,1:01:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对妇女选择堕胎的基本权利持敌对态度的法官们{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who are hostile to a woman's fundamental right to choose abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.89,1:01:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎诉讼很像“芝麻街”（少儿节目）\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Abortion litigation is a lot like Sesame Street{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.49,1:02:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你得学会数数\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You got to learn to count{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.26,1:02:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一重要的数字是5\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the only number that's important is five{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.48,1:02:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,最高法院有5票吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Are there five votes on the Supreme Court?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.04,1:02:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,5票将会推翻罗案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Five votes that would overturn Roe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.52,1:02:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他是这个职位的最佳人选{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}He is the best person for this position{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.20,1:02:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,总统提名克拉伦斯•托马斯为最高法院大法官\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The president nominated Clarence Thomas to the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.60,1:02:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为他会是否决罗案的第5票\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I thought he would be the fifth vote to overrule Roe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.64,1:02:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得，法庭上有一种沉默是显而易见的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I remember there was a silence in the courtroom that was palpable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.35,1:02:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔伯特女士\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Ms. Kolbert{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.34,1:02:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法官大人，希望法庭满意留意{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.38,1:02:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的宪法赋予政府的权力{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Whether our Constitution endows government with the power to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.64,1:02:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是强迫妇女继续怀孕，还是违背其意愿终止妊娠{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}force a woman to continue or to end a pregnancy against her will{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.84,1:02:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是本案的核心问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is the central question in this case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.94,1:02:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,然后美国副检察长站起来争辩说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then the Solicitor General of the United States stood up and argued{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.13,1:02:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“罗诉韦德案”应该被推翻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that Roe versus Wade ought to be overturned{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.42,1:02:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…国家确实对潜在的生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…the State does have a compelling interest in the potential life,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.28,1:02:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对胎儿的生命有着强烈兴趣，这种兴趣贯穿整个怀孕期{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in fetal life, and that interest runs throughout pregnancy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.82,1:03:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但是，我希望法院理解\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But I wanted the Court to understand the implications{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.60,1:03:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,改变一项“对妇女具有保护意义”的标准的含义\N{\fnarial\fs12\}of changing a standard that was very protective for women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.32,1:03:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}本庭已经认识到，自主权、身体完整性{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This Court has recognized that the rights of autonomy, bodily integrity,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.99,1:03:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和平等权，是我们自由意志的核心{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and equality are central to our notions of ordered liberty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.50,1:03:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}罗案是这些利益的核心{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Roe lies at the heart of those interests{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.07,1:03:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,因为，归根结底\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Because, ultimately,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.31,1:03:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,堕胎与妇女是否应该接受特殊的医疗程序无关\N{\fnarial\fs12\}abortion is not about whether or not women should have particular medical procedures{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.96,1:03:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它是关于平等的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's about equality{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.62,1:03:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这是关于生命的观点，关于应该是谁来做重要决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's about a view of life, about who should make important decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.15,1:03:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,很少有人会知道\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's very rare that you know the date{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.48,1:03:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,最高法院将要判决的日期\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the Supreme Court is going to issue a decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.43,1:03:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这个案子将会判决，但是不知道什么时候\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know that the case will be decided, but you don't know when{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.30,1:03:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,但这一次我们知道什么时候，因为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But this time we knew when, because{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.30,1:03:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他们听到的所有其他案件都已经判决了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}every other case that they heard that term had already been decided{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.58,1:03:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们现在在最高法院外等候宣判结果{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We're waiting outside the Supreme Court now for the announcement of the Court's decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.49,1:04:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，外面有大批媒体等着\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So, there were media trucks parked outside{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.77,1:04:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都准备好了，等待着对罗案的判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Everybody was ready and waiting for the overturning of Roe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.12,1:04:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发布91-45号命令{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Release 91-45 Standing Orders{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.28,1:04:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,法院书记官递给我一份判决书的副本\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The clerk of the court handed me a copy of the decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.65,1:04:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,坦白说，我在很多方面都很困惑\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And frankly I was confused in many respects{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.19,1:04:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，这是一个5、60页的意见，很复杂\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know, it's a 50, 60 page opinion. It's complicated{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.94,1:04:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须阅读并理解它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You have to read it and understand it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.12,1:04:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时，我被派去\N{\fnarial\fs12\}At the same time, I'm shepherded out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.95,1:04:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,和美国媒体谈论刚刚发生的事情\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to talk to American media about what just happened{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.36,1:04:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我是凯瑟琳•科尔伯特，我是宾夕法尼亚州{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I am Kathryn Kolbert. I am counsel of record on behalf of{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.14,1:04:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}计划生育协会和其他堕胎诊所的法律顾问{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Planned Parenthood and the other abortion clinics in Pennsylvania{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.45,1:04:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个非常模棱两可的判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was a very ambiguous decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.04,1:04:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,三名共和党任命的法官聚在一起\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Three Republican-appointed justices had gotten together,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.42,1:04:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们决定，与其推翻罗案的判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and they decided that rather than overturn Roe against Wade,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.50,1:04:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不如用他们称之为“不当负担标准”重新修订它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they were going to reformulate it with what they called the undue burden standard{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.54,1:05:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，法院维持了堕胎的权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So the Court upheld the right to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.88,1:05:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但是新的标准意味着，各州可以采取措施\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But the new standard meant that states can undertake to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.69,1:05:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,说服妇女怀孕到足月\N{\fnarial\fs12\}persuade a woman to carry a pregnancy to term,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.85,1:05:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他们不能阻止妇女选择堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but they cannot prevent a woman from choosing abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.18,1:05:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,在“罗诉韦德案”中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Under Roe versus Wade,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.13,1:05:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,大多数的堕胎限制都是违宪的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}most abortion restrictions were unconstitutional{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.72,1:05:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在凯西案中，最高法院基本上认为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In Casey, the Court basically said that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.32,1:05:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,各州在限制堕胎方面，拥有比罗案判决更多的自由\N{\fnarial\fs12\}states had the latitude to restrict abortion in more ways than under Roe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.13,1:05:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}多种多样的限制，等待期，知情同意{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Many, many kinds of restrictions, waiting periods, informed consent{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.34,1:05:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在罗案判决中被发现的违宪行为，已得到了法院的证实{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Things found unconstitutional under Roe have been validated by this Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.49,1:05:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因此，我们的处境要比过去糟得多{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And therefore we are much worse off than we have been in the paSt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.70,1:05:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那时候，你知道，我想这真的很可怕\N{\fnarial\fs12\}At the time, I thought, you know, this is really horrible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.00,1:05:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在女性的道路上设置障碍…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…to place roadblocks in the path of women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.23,1:05:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但是，不管负担标准给我们带来了什么问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But whatever problems the undue burden standard gave us,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.94,1:05:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,它仍然比完全禁止堕胎要好\N{\fnarial\fs12\}it was still preferable than a total outlaw of abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.21,1:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,对于需要医疗手术的女性来说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For a woman in need of a medical procedure,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.98,1:06:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,一个很大的区别是，不得不接受手术\N{\fnarial\fs12\}there's a big difference between having to jump through hoops{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.61,1:06:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,和根本不能接受手术，是不一样的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and not being able to get the procedure at all{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.70,1:06:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}四名法官表示，“罗诉韦德案”必须被推翻{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Four justices have said Roe versus Wade must be overturned{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.44,1:06:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们只需再多一次机会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}All it's going to take is one more{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.65,1:06:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我只能希望布什总统能够再次当选{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I can only hope that President Bush gets reelected{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.78,1:06:18.74,自定义,,0,0,0,,克林顿总统就任
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.02,1:06:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}总统是否认为女性有选择权至关重要{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It makes a difference whether the president believes in a woman's right to choose{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.58,1:06:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而我相信{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.75,1:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在克林顿夫妇周围\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There was some momentum{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.25,1:06:34.54,自定义,,0,0,0,,伊丽莎白•纳什   古特马赫研究所
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.18,1:06:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,有一些支持堕胎权利的势头\N{\fnarial\fs12\}around the Clintons and support for abortion rights{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.05,1:06:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我很荣幸地提名鲁思•金斯伯格•马尔科姆为最高法院法官{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I am proud to nominate Judge Ruth Bader Ginsburg to the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.49,1:06:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}女性能作为决策者，是男女平等的要素{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is essential to woman's equality with man that she be the decision-maker{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.90,1:06:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我很荣幸能提名斯蒂芬•布雷耶法官{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm proud to nominate Judge Stephen Breyer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.53,1:06:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在美国最高法院任职{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to serve on the United States Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.84,1:06:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一些法案在联邦层面上悬而未决，以保护堕胎的权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And there were bills pending at the federal level to protect access to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.53,1:07:02.56,自定义,,0,0,0,,克里斯•史密斯   共和党国会议员
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.40,1:07:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}克林顿团队已经开始系统性地对未出生的孩子发动战争{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Clinton team has begun to systematically wage war against unborn children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.64,1:07:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,反对堕胎的人正在寻找阻止这一势头的方法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And abortion opponents were looking for a way to stop this momentum{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.94,1:07:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他们想出了这个新主意\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So they came up with this new idea{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.86,1:07:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,并在后来的堕胎问题上进行了研究\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and they honed in on later abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.84,1:07:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们特别提出了“分期堕胎”这个术语\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Specifically they came up with the term "partial birth abortion"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.55,1:07:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大家部分留在这边，其他去另一边，好吗？不是所有人{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Some of you stay on this side, some of you go on the other side, okay? Not everyone{\r} 
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.64,1:07:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}试着分散开来，把标志尽可能放到更多地方{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Try and spread out and get the signs as many places as possible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.42,1:07:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在亲生命运动中，“分期生育”像野火一样迅速蔓延\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Partial birth took off like wildfire inside the pro-life movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.94,1:07:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,它使人的良心感到恐惧和震惊\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It so horrified and shocked the conscience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.20,1:07:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,剥夺了计划生育和堕胎医生的尊严\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and stripped this veil of respectability from Planned Parenthood and the abortionists{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.00,1:07:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太可怕了，我们要站在哪一边？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's terrible. Which side of the fence are we gonna be on?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.93,1:07:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须教育公众\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We had to educate the public{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.07,1:07:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们是否要继续支持美国的儿童杀戮，并称之为选择？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Are we gonna continue to support child killing in America and call it choice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.22,1:07:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们制造了一个问题，并且把它强加给了美国\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We made it an issue. We forced it on America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.60,1:08:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是“分期堕胎”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is partial birth abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.03,1:08:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}堕胎者用镊子夹住婴儿的腿{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The abortionist grabs the live baby's legs with forceps{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.34,1:08:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党人提出了分期堕胎法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Republicans introduced the partial birth abortion law,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.90,1:08:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管没有这样的东西\N{\fnarial\fs12\}even though there's no such thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.00,1:08:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他们编造了这个词，这是一个策略\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They made up the word and it was a strategy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.04,1:08:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,真正挑战晚期堕胎何时被允许的问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that really went to challenging the question of when late abortion would be permitted{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.97,1:08:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,有了这个主意，如果你能把可堕胎的时间越往早推\N{\fnarial\fs12\}With the idea that, if you could push it earlier and earlier,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.41,1:08:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你就可以消除一些堕胎行为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you could eliminate a number of abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.01,1:08:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们马上就知道这将是一个大问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we knew immediately that this was going to be a huge issue{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.85,1:08:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}堕胎倡导者声称，为了禁止分期堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Abortion advocates are claiming that, by banning partial-birth abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.65,1:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们正在对“罗诉韦德案”发起直接攻击{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we are mounting a direct attack on Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.87,1:08:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对他们来说，从来没有不适合堕胎的时候{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For them, there is never an instance when abortion is inappropriate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.73,1:08:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对他们来说，堕胎的权利是绝对的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For them, the right to abortion is absolute{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.50,1:08:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}无论什么时候，无论什么原因，不管什么方式{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}at whatever time, for whatever reason, and in whatever way,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.45,1:08:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都由妇女或堕胎医生选择{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a woman or an abortionist chooses{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.37,1:08:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,90%的堕胎妇女都是在妊娠的前三个月\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Ninety percent of women who have an abortion have it in the first trimester{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.16,1:08:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,这是绝大多数的女性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's the vast majority of women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.52,1:09:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在20周内做的人比例更小\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then a smaller proportion have it before 20 weeks{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.16,1:09:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,在20到24周之间的，我们估计在1%左右\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Between 20 and 24 weeks, we're at probably about one percent{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.48,1:09:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,随着孕期的增加，堕胎的比例就会越小\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And then, as we get further along, we're getting to smaller and smaller numbers,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.70,1:09:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,会达到最低点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}exceedingly low numbers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.60,1:09:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,所以大多数的堕胎都是在怀孕的前三个月\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So the majority of abortions are in the first trimester{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.69,1:09:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们大部分时间都在谈论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But we spend most of our time talking about{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.10,1:09:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,发生在怀孕中期和晚期时的堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}abortions that happened in the second and third trimester{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.72,1:09:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这是反堕胎运动的策略之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And this is one of the strategies of the anti-choice movement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.06,1:09:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我们称其为“分期堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Why do we call something the partial-birth abortion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.29,1:09:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上这不是医学术语\N{\fnarial\fs12\}when really that's not a medical term{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.32,1:09:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你总是追着你对手的弱点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You always go after your enemy where they're the weakest.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.54,1:09:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他们知道，一旦我们赢了，在第9个月\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they know that, once we win, in the ninth month,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.60,1:09:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下的纸牌屋就会崩溃\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the rest of the card house comes crumbling down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.94,1:09:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我们破坏了他们的论点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We destroy their arguments{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.94,1:09:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,他们创造了一个故事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They created a narrative that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.69,1:09:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,怀孕后期的女性杀死他们的孩子，因为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}women late in pregnancies were killing their babies 'cause they,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.84,1:09:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，她们想去健身房\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you know, wanted to go to the gym instead{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.93,1:09:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,完全是子虚乌有的事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Totally false. Doesn't happen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.86,1:09:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,但是没有30秒的声音片段来对抗图像\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But there's no 30-second sound bite to counter that image{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.50,1:09:56.30,自定义,,0,0,0,,（如果你感到这很冒犯，恭喜，你是有良心的）
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.50,1:09:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他们很擅长制造光影形象\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They were very good at creating optics,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.92,1:09:59.50,自定义,,0,0,0,,（敬请克林顿总统签署1833号法令）
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.48,1:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,制造舆论来支持他们的观点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}creating language that supported their point of view{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.01,1:10:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们必须想办法在政治上挑战它\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so we had to figure out how to challenge it politically{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.68,1:10:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能够把克林顿总统介绍给\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we were able to introduce President Clinton{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.43,1:10:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,那些将会受到法律影响的妇女\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to women who would be affected by the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.60,1:10:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那些很晚才堕胎的妇女，或者\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Women who were losing pregnancies very late or{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.26,1:10:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,怀孕时发现胎儿畸形严重的妇女\N{\fnarial\fs12\}finding themselves carrying a pregnancy with very severe fetal anomalies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.37,1:10:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}早上好，感谢小组委员会的邀请{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Good morning. I'd like to thank the subcommittee for inviting me here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.50,1:10:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我去做了7个月的常规超声波检查{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I went in for a routine seven-month ultrasound{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.48,1:10:28.41,自定义,,0,0,0,,泰米•沃特斯    禁止分期堕胎听证会
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.42,1:10:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们说，“这看起来不错”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They were saying, "This looks good. This looks good"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.34,1:10:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}突然，他们变得非常安静{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Then suddenly, they got really quiet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.80,1:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}医生说，“你女儿没有眼睛，她的心脏…”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The doctor said, "Your daughter has no eyes, and her heart{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.68,1:10:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}“其他的主要器官也在衰竭”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and other major organs are also failing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.58,1:10:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}“你的孩子将无法存活”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And your child will not live"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.76,1:10:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我记得我只是看着窗外，我看不到任何人{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I remember just looking out the window. I couldn't look at anybody{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.84,1:11:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}于是我的婆婆问，“我们要继续吗？她还要继续妊娠吗？”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So my mother-in-law asked, "Do we go on? Does she have to go on?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.46,1:11:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个可怕的问题影响了上百个美国人{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This terrible problem affects a few hundred Americans{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.17,1:11:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每一年{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}every year,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.03,1:11:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们迫切地想要自己的孩子{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}who desperately want their children,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.64,1:11:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们正在努力建立家庭，并努力巩固他们的家庭{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}are trying to building families and are trying to strengthen their families{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.65,1:11:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们不应该成为一场更大的辩论中的棋子{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they should not become pawns in a larger debate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.93,1:11:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因此，我别无选择，只能否决该法案{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And therefore I had no choice but to veto the bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.25,1:11:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就在几分钟前，在我与这些家庭见面之前，我否决了它{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I vetoed it just a few minutes ago before I met with these families{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.25,1:11:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,比尔•克林顿否决了它，但它真的传播开了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Bill Clinton vetoed it, but it really spread{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.18,1:11:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们开始看到这些法案的新版本\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And we started to see new iterations of these bills,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.09,1:11:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,使用略微不同的语言，以便承受法律上的挑战\N{\fnarial\fs12\}using slightly different language, in order to withstand a legal challenge{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.98,1:11:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这个国家，允许牺牲儿童是可耻的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's a shame that child sacrifice can be allowed in this country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.89,1:11:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们因为发表和展示堕胎的真相而被逮捕{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are being arrested for speaking and showing the truth of abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.65,1:11:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要禁止“分期堕胎”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We need to ban partial-birth abortions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.61,1:11:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信禁止分期堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe banning partial-birth abortions would be{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.73,1:12:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,是减少美国堕胎数量的积极步骤\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a positive step toward reducing the number of abortions in America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.60,1:12:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能够让乔治•W•布什以这样的承诺当选\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We were able to get George W. Bush elected with the promise that,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.81,1:12:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,如果再有其他禁令，他就会通过并签署\N{\fnarial\fs12\}if we got another ban, he'd pass it again and sign it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.38,1:12:14.61,自定义,,0,0,0,,分期堕胎禁令  2003年
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.38,1:12:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他签署了联邦禁令，使之成为法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And he signed the federal ban into law,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.84,1:12:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,并将其升至最高法院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and it went to the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.33,1:12:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}反堕胎派滚蛋了！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Anti-choice has got to go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.36,1:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}堕胎的问题摆在最高法院面前{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The issue of abortion's before the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.82,1:12:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}法官桑德拉•戴•奥康纳今早宣布，她将退休{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Justice Sandra Day O'Connor announced this morning that she will retire{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.29,1:12:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}首席大法官威廉•伦奎斯特已过世{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Chief Justice William Rehnquist has died{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.17,1:12:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}提名权是总统最重要的职责之一{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The nomination power is one of the most serious responsibilities of a president{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.40,1:12:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我将向最高法院提名罗伯茨法官{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I will nominate Judge Roberts to the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.56,1:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}首席大法官罗伯茨的同事{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And Chief Justice Roberts will have as his colleague{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.36,1:12:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将是联邦党人协会骄傲的一员{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a proud member of The Federalist Society,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.90,1:12:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}小山姆•阿利托法官{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Judge Sam Alito, Jr.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.12,1:12:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,今天，最高法院以5比4通过了一项里程碑意义的裁决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In a 5-4 landmark decision,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.83,1:12:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,新当选的保守派法官多数支持在全国范围内\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the Court's new conservative majority today upheld a nationwide ban{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.00,1:12:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,禁止一项被批评者称为“分期堕胎”的程序\N{\fnarial\fs12\}on a procedure critics call partial-birth abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.84,1:12:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在法庭上，愤怒的大法官鲁思•巴德•金斯伯格\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In court, an angry Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.68,1:13:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,用不同寻常的步骤大声朗读她的异议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}took the unusual step of reading her dissent aloud{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.85,1:13:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我强烈反对今天的意见\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I strongly dissent from today's opinion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.54,1:13:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“分期堕胎”禁令只能被理解为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act cannot be understood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.26,1:13:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,试图削弱“罗诉韦德案”中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}as anything other than an effort to chip away{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.25,1:13:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,宣布的一项权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}at a right declared in Roe v. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.73,1:13:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}罗诉韦德案{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Roe versus Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.20,1:13:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}阻止了我们禁止堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}prevents us from prohibiting abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.50,1:13:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但它确实允许我们{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But it does allow us,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.13,1:13:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}允许国家做一些事情来保护生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the states, to…do some things to protect life,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.30,1:13:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果它们可以表明存在着令人信服的国家利益{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}if they can show there is a compelling state interest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.18,1:13:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,州长里克•佩里希望终止生殖健康医疗\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Governor Rick Perry wanted to end access to reproductive health care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.96,1:13:51.40,自定义,,0,0,0,,塞西尔•理查德斯    计划生育协会前主席
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.96,1:13:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在共和党的领导下，由于立法机构不成比例\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And because the legislature is so disproportionately led by the Republican party,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.05,1:13:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他们提出了堕胎限制，这是全国最极端的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they proposed abortion restrictions, which were the most extreme in the country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.57,1:14:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,国会第二号法案就是一个很好的例子\N{\fnarial\fs12\}House Bill 2 was a good example of these kinds of laws{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.89,1:14:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这类法律在共和党控制的许多州都得到了通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that were being passed in many states controlled by the Republicans{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.37,1:14:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,法律真正关注的是堕胎可以在哪里进行\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Laws that really focused on where the abortion could be performed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.96,1:14:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,以及对医生办公室或手术中心的规定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and regulations to either the doctor's office or a surgical center{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.26,1:14:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}感谢您致电西南妇女外科中心{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Thank you for calling the Southwestern Women's Surgery Center{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.41,1:14:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我是艾丽西娅，能帮你什么忙吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is Alicia. How may I help you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.72,1:14:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是所谓的陷阱法：\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is what are known as TRAP laws: {\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.00,1:14:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对堕胎机构的针对性监管\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Targeted Regulation of Abortion Providers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.19,1:14:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这些法律的目的是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the purpose of these laws is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.94,1:14:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,尽可能地使提供堕胎服务变得困难\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to make it as difficult as possible to provide abortion services,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.78,1:14:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,从而禁止尽可能多的堕胎\N{\fnarial\fs12\}prohibit as many abortions as you can,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.06,1:14:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,让发生的手术尽可能的昂贵\N{\fnarial\fs12\}make the ones that do occur as expensive as possible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.67,1:14:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,他们所做的很明显\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's so obvious what they're doing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.02,1:14:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我的目标是，让堕胎在任何阶段都成为过去{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}My goal is to make abortion, at any stage, a thing of the paSt.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.04,1:14:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这些限制措施将导致\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So these restrictions would shut down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.08,1:14:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,德克萨斯州数十家妇女健康中心关闭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}dozens of women's health centers all across Texas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.35,1:14:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么参议员温迪•戴维斯\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that's why Senator Wendy Davis{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.62,1:14:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,决定站出来为妇女的权利而斗争\N{\fnarial\fs12\}decided to stand up and fight for the rights of women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.35,1:15:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这个法案被提交到参议院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So this bill went to the Senate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.05,1:15:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但是，因为这是会议的最后一天，时间紧迫\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But, because it was the final day of the session, the clock was ticking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.49,1:15:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这给了我一个阻挠议事的机会\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that gave me an opportunity for the filibuster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.40,1:15:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}各位，我今天站在这里…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Members, I'm rising on the floor today{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.41,1:15:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着我有大约13个小时的谈话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That meant I had about 13 hours of talking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.77,1:15:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,来确保这项法案不会通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to make sure that this bill did not pass{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.88,1:15:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,德克萨斯州规定你不能喝一口水\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The rules in Texas say that you cannot have a sip of water,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.81,1:15:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能饮用任何东西\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you cannot have anything to drink,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.35,1:15:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能靠在桌子上\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you cannot lean on your desk{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.50,1:15:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当然也不能离开地板去洗手间\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and you certainly cannot leave the floor to go to the restroom{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.83,1:15:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我脚上穿着一双跑鞋，带着一个导尿管袋\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So I had a pair of running shoes on my feet and I had a catheter bag{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.26,1:15:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,那天早上大约6点钟，一位医生过来\N{\fnarial\fs12\}A doctor had come over at about six o'clock that morning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.45,1:15:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,插上一根导管，这样我就能熬过这一天了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and inserted a catheter so that I'd be able to make it through the day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.06,1:15:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}温迪 • 戴维斯参议员必须坚持到午夜{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Senator Wendy Davis must make it to midnight{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.58,1:15:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}特别会议到此结束{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That is the end of the special session{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.68,1:15:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}实际上，她是在浪费时间，耗费钟点{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Essentially she's wasting time, running out the clock{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.82,1:15:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她是怎么做的？现在{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The way she's doing that? Right now,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.24,1:15:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她正在读反对这项立法的德州妇女的信件{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}she's reading letters from Texas women who oppose this legislation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.03,1:16:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…为了让她们的声音被听到{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…in order for their voices to be heard{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.61,1:16:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}-…告诉我，任何妊娠都将非常…{\i0}\N- 而且冗长的演说迅速传播开\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- …told me any pregnancy will be very…- And the filibuster went viral{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.00,1:16:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,她不仅是一位反对这项法案的女性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not only was she a woman opposing the bill,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.70,1:16:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,而且是这个房间里仅有的几个女性之一\N{\fnarial\fs12\}but she was one of the only women in the room{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.25,1:16:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个互联网时刻\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was an internet moment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.76,1:16:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,奥巴马：#奥斯丁（德州省会）今夜会有特别的事情发生
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.44,1:16:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,人们把他们的孩子留给邻居照看\N{\fnarial\fs12\}People had left their kids with their neighbors{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.85,1:16:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,然后开上几小时的车去到奥斯丁那里\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and driven hours to Austin to be there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.76,1:16:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,学生们离开了他们的大学校园\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Students had left their college campuses{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.65,1:16:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,来到奥斯丁，聆听温迪的长篇大论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and came to Austin to hear Wendy filibuster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.18,1:16:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些德州人依赖少数的……{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}These are Texans who relied on the minority{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.70,1:16:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我是德克萨斯人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm a Texan{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.30,1:16:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,从来没见过像我们在那里看到的那种激进主义浪潮\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Never seen the outpouring of activism like we saw there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.95,1:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你简直进不了议会大厦\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You literally could not get in the capitol{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.00,1:16:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,所有走廊都是人，每个房间都满了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Every annex was full, every room was full{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.47,1:16:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这是非同寻常的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was extraordinary{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.36,1:16:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她做出的另一个裁决是，如果有…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…another ruling she made was if there was a{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.26,1:16:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,大约在午夜前的15分钟\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And about 15 minutes before midnight,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.44,1:16:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,程序性的规则被打破了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}procedural rules of order were broken{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.91,1:16:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}第三…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…and the third{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.92,1:17:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,为了结束我的冗长演说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in order to bring my filibuster to an end{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.28,1:17:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在场的人都知道，他们违反规定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the people who were there understood that rules were being broken{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.70,1:17:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,是为了让反对法案的人禁声\N{\fnarial\fs12\}in order to silence opposition to a bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.54,1:17:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在与参议员协商之后…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}After consultation with the parliamentarian and after{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.60,1:17:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,而且他们已经受够了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And they'd had enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.90,1:17:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…被采取，并维持{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…well taken and is sustained{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.90,1:17:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}扯淡！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.36,1:17:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}主席承认参议员……{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The chair recognizes Senator{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.18,1:17:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}让她说！让她说！让她说！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Let her speak! Let her speak! Let her speak!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.50,1:17:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,温迪！温迪！温迪！温迪！{\i1}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Wendy! Wendy! Wendy! Wendy!{\r\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.61,1:17:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们开始尖叫时\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And as they began to scream,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.45,1:17:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,走廊里的每个人都开始尖叫\N{\fnarial\fs12\}everyone up and down the hallways began to scream,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.21,1:17:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,圆形大厅的每一层，以及国会大厦外的草坪上\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and at every level of the rotunda and outside on the capitol lawn{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.21,1:17:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以真切地感受到\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I could literally feel{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.02,1:17:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的声音和能量的振动\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the vibration of their voices and their energy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.17,1:17:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,还有他们脚步声的冲击\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and the pounding of their feet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.18,1:18:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}请保持秩序，我们正在投票中{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If I can have order. We are in the middle of a vote{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.05,1:18:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}秘书已经开始投票了{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The secretary has started the vote{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.13,1:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,它拖延了足够的时间\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It ate up enough of the clock{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.40,1:18:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,最后的投票直到12:03还没完成\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the final vote wasn't taken until 12:03{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.79,1:18:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}众位，现在已经是午夜了，所以…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Members, it's now past midnight. And so…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.18,1:18:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这也被称为“人民阻挠议事”，确实如此\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it became known as the people's filibuster. Rightly so{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.55,1:18:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是参议员温迪•戴维斯的原话，好吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is straight from Senator Wendy Davis, okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.09,1:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}等会儿再鼓掌{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Hold your applause{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.10,1:18:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}首先，“我爱你们”…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}First, I love you guys. Okay?{\r}  
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.92,1:18:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们也爱你，温迪！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We love you, too, Wendy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.02,1:18:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“因此，副州长同意5号禁令已死”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"So the lieutenant governor has agreed that SB-5 is dead"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.49,1:18:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,前几天在参议院阻挠议事的那个女人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The woman who filibustered the Senate the other day,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.29,1:19:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她出生在艰难的环境中\N{\fnarial\fs12\}she was born into difficult circumstances{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.28,1:19:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一个单身女人的女儿\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She's the daughter of a single woman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.82,1:19:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她自己也是个十几岁的母亲\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She was a teenage mother herself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.25,1:19:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,她最终从哈佛法学院毕业\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She managed to eventually graduate from Harvard Law School{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.96,1:19:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,并在德州参议院任职\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and serve in the Texas Senate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.14,1:19:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,不幸的是，她没有从自己的例子中吸取教训\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's unfortunate that she hasn't learned from her own example{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.81,1:19:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都必须有机会充分发挥自己的潜能\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that every life must be given a chance to realize its full potential{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.70,1:19:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,每一个生命都很重要\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and that every life matters{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.50,1:19:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们成功地扼杀了这个法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We had successfully killed the bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.46,1:19:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但是几天之内我们就被召回了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But we were called right back within a few days{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.41,1:19:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，这一次没办法阻挠议事\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And, of course, this time there was no way to filibuster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.02,1:19:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ 所有的婴儿都到哪里去了？♪{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Where have all the babies gone?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.95,1:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪我为每一个人祈祷天堂♪{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I pray to heaven for every one{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.16,1:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,准备好再做一次\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Get ready to do it all again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.87,1:19:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,州长里克•佩里在今晚早些时候召开了一次特别会议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Governor Rick Perry called a special session early this evening{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.40,1:19:53.37,自定义,,0,0,0,,（有关堕胎程序，机构，设施，机构处罚的规定）
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.58,1:19:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们讨论了选择权问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We talked about the choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.49,1:19:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为如果母亲和婴儿对话，说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Do you think if the mother had a conversation with the baby and said,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.68,1:20:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“你知道，现在把你生下来真的不太方便”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"You know, this just isn't really convenient to give birth to you right now{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.34,1:20:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“你介意死吗？”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Do you mind dying?"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.81,1:20:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 我再也受不了了！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I can't take it anymore!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.63,1:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我认为…… \N{\i1}- 简直强词夺理！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- I think…  - That was very offensive!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.27,1:20:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我想婴儿会说——\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think that baby would say--{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.99,1:20:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 这是对女性的人身攻击！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is an assault on women!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.72,1:20:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我不生那些老乡的气，我为她祈祷\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I don't get mad with those folks. I pray for her{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.75,1:20:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 你辜负了德克萨斯！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You are failing Texas!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.78,1:20:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,再过几分钟\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In just a few moments,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.82,1:20:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要投票表决一项法案\N{\fnarial\fs12\}we are going to vote on a bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.73,1:20:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这将使我们产生深刻的分歧\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that has deeply and profoundly divided us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.79,1:20:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,将我们以党派划分…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Separating us by political party{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.86,1:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,以性别\N{\fnarial\fs12\}by gender{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.54,1:20:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,以生活经历……\N{\fnarial\fs12\}by life experience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.81,1:20:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,以维系我们的信仰\N{\fnarial\fs12\}by what our religious beliefs bind us to{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.26,1:20:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今生都不能！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Not in this life!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.10,1:20:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都相信人生的美丽和奇迹\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We all believe in the beauty and the wonder that is human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.81,1:21:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也相信在这里的女性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But I also believe that women already here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.65,1:21:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,都是美丽的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}are beautiful{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.74,1:21:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,她们应该活下去\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that they deserve to live,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.38,1:21:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她们应该决定自己生活的方向\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they deserve to determine the direction of their lives,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.94,1:21:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,她们应该被当作是完整的人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}they deserve to be recognized as full people{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.91,1:21:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,完全有能力做出艰难的决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}fully capable of making difficult decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.08,1:21:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在她们的家人，她们的医生和上帝的帮助下\N{\fnarial\fs12\}with the help of their family, their doctor and their God{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.81,1:21:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,温迪！温迪！温迪！温迪！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Wendy! Wendy! Wendy! Wendy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.67,1:21:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,任何女人都不应该被别人评判\N{\fnarial\fs12\}No woman should be judged by someone else,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.21,1:21:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,被那些相信他们会做出不同决定人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}someone who believes they would have made a different decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.16,1:21:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,任何女人都不应该被别人评判\N{\fnarial\fs12\}No woman should be judged by someone else,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.88,1:21:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这些决定从来都不容易\N{\fnarial\fs12\}because these decisions are never ever easy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.11,1:21:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,它们既不是随意的，也不是草率的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They're not made casually or quickly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.90,1:22:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们这些在参议院的人，应该\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And those of us in the Senate should refuse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.09,1:22:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,拒绝随意或迅速地做出这个决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to make this decision casually or quickly{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.24,1:22:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,因为关乎德州未来的斗争才刚刚开始\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Because the fight for the future of Texas is just beginning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.75,1:22:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢，总统先生，谢谢各位\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Thank you, Mr. President. Thank you, members{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.58,1:22:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,现在有19票赞成，11票反对，国会法案二最终通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There being 19 ayes and 11 nays, House Bill 2 is finally passed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.65,1:22:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不会回去！我们不会回去！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We won't go back! We won't go back!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.26,1:22:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,提高本州妇女的护理质量是我们的责任\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is our responsibility to improve the quality of care for women in the state{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.66,1:22:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，一直以来都有人认为\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Of course, the argument was made all along that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.79,1:22:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这样做是为了妇女的健康\N{\fnarial\fs12\}somehow this is being done in the interests of women's health{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.47,1:22:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管这种说法遭到了令人难以置信的科学反驳\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And in spite of incredible scientific pushback to that statement,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.83,1:22:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,国会法案二通过\N{\fnarial\fs12\}House Bill 2 passed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.59,1:22:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,耻辱！耻辱！耻辱！\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Shame! Shame! Shame!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.23,1:23:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这项法律生效后，本州半数以上的堕胎诊所关闭了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The law went into effect and over half of our abortion clinics in the state closed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.13,1:23:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从41个诊所变成了19个\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We went from 41 clinics to 19{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.55,1:23:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是法律实施的结果\N{\fnarial\fs12\}as a consequence of the implementation of the law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.52,1:23:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在德克萨斯州中部，已经一家诊所都没有了\N{\fnarial\fs12\}In central Texas, there were no clinics left open{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.08,1:23:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这很让人泄气\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And that was pretty demoralizing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.18,1:23:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但确实发生了一些非常重要的事情\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But there was something really important that had happened{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.34,1:23:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,从国家层面唤醒了我们，对于女性受到现实侵犯的认识\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We as a state woke up to the reality of an assault on women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.60,1:23:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我们清醒地意识到我们的力量\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We woke up to the reality of our power{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.31,1:23:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一种持续壮大的力量\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And it's a power that has continued to grow{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.55,1:23:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这是近十年来的第一起重大堕胎案件\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The first major abortion case in almost a decade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.62,1:23:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它以德州的一个案例为中心，该案已经迫使诊所关闭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It centers on a case in Texas that has already forced clinics to close{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.32,1:23:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,并可能迫使更多的诊所关闭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and could force even more to close down as well{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.12,1:24:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,利害关系是巨大的，不仅是对德州的女性而言\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The stakes are huge. And they're not just huge for Texas women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.68,1:24:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,对于全国各地的女性来说都是利害巨大\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They're huge for women all over the country{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.29,1:24:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}反选择就是反女人！{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Anti-choice! Anti-women!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.06,1:24:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,如果法庭确认德州的法律\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If the Court affirms the law in Texas,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.62,1:24:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我毫不怀疑其他州会立即效仿\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I have no doubt that other states will immediately follow suit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.32,1:24:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,所以很多女性将不再有堕胎的机会\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so many women will no longer have access to abortion care{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.06,1:24:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这就像一个完美的对照实验，不是吗？\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's almost like a perfect controlled experiment, isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.30,1:24:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像你让法律生效，12家诊所关门\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's like you put the law into effect, twelve clinics closed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.37,1:24:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,把法律从事实中抽离，他们重新开放\N{\fnarial\fs12\}To take the law out of the fact, they reopen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.50,1:24:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是绝对正确的…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}That's absolutely correct{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.45,1:24:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我参加了辩论，我被只有一位女性法官的法庭\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I went to the argument, and I was struck by the difference{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.03,1:24:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,和有三位女性法官的法庭之间的差异所震惊\N{\fnarial\fs12\}between a Court with one female justice and a Court with three{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.26,1:24:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我能承受这个负担吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Can I walk through the burden?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.39,1:24:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为了接受两天的治疗，她不得不跋涉200英里{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}She has to travel 200 miles to get two days of treatment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.37,1:25:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有多少女性得走上100英里以上{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}How many women are located over 100 miles{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.21,1:25:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,女人们可以互相强加给对方观点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The women could reinforce each other's viewpoints{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.37,1:25:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}利益和负担之间有某种关联，不是吗？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There has to some tie between benefit and burden, doesn't there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.81,1:25:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为他们非常善于，抛开所有这些似是而非的论点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think they were very good at throwing aside all of these specious arguments,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.05,1:25:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,使其看上去像是国家在真正关心妇女\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the state was making that really all they cared about was women{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.96,1:25:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这对ASC（日间手术中心）和准入特权都有好处{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}There are benefits for the ASC and admitting-privileges{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.99,1:25:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}好处是什么… 有什么证据…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What is the benefit…What evidence is there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.03,1:25:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,就是说，你知道，现在的情况是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Just said, You know, what's going on here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.26,1:25:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你是在让女性更难做出自己的选择…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}is you are making it more difficult for women to exercise their choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.83,1:25:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是风险最低的程序之一{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}This is one of the lowest-risk procedures{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.34,1:25:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将尊重她的决定\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…and we are going to respect her decision{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.09,1:25:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这项法律只针对堕胎{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…this law was targeted at abortion only{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.31,1:25:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}许多手术的风险要大得多：{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…many procedures are much higher risk:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.88,1:25:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}结肠镜，吸脂术，我们还可以继续{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}colonoscopies, liposuctions{\r} We could go on and on{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.62,1:25:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须告诉你们，他们接受了这个论点\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And I have to tell you, they took over that argument{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.37,1:25:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这是关于，一个女人\N{\fnarial\fs12\}What it's about is that a woman has{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.45,1:25:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,有为自己做出选择的基本权利\N{\fnarial\fs12\}a fundamental right to make this choice for herself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.04,1:25:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天，最高法院废除了德州的一项法律{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Today the Supreme Court struck down a Texas law{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.74,1:26:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}该法对诊所和医生施加了严格的要求{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that imposed strict requirements on clinics and doctors,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.94,1:26:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}认为这些限制给宪法赋予的堕胎权带来了不必要的负担{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}finding those limits place an undue burden on the constitutional right to abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.34,1:26:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说，这个决定的亮点是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}For me, the highlight of that decision was{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.50,1:26:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,大法官们将实际的医学和科学结合起来\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the justices' incorporation of actual medicine and science{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.77,1:26:21.32,自定义,,0,0,0,,（许多包括接生在内的医疗程序具有重大风险）
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.42,1:26:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们看到一个关于堕胎的决策，说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We've seen a decision about abortion that says,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.34,1:26:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“如果你要提出要求\N{\fnarial\fs12\}"If you're going to make a claim,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.89,1:26:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这个要求必须是准确符合事实的”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}the claim must be factually accurate"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.42,1:26:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实是\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But the reality is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.36,1:26:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,法官的任命是高度政治化的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that the appointing of our justices is highly political{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.85,1:26:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，在任何时候，法院的平衡都会发生变化\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And so, at any time, the balance of the Court can change{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.83,1:26:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,下一次的决定可能会有所不同\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And the decision may be different next time{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.10,1:26:51.95,自定义,,0,0,0,,（真相是，堕胎的并发症很少见，也很少会有危险）
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.46,1:26:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,最高法院在赫勒斯泰特的判决\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The Supreme Court decision in Hellerstedt{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.52,1:26:59.86,自定义,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔·特拜斯    国家生命权利会主席
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.25,1:27:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,再一次激发了亲生命派人士的积极性\N{\fnarial\fs12\}motivated pro-life people, reinforced, once again,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.49,1:27:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们想要改变法律，我们必须改变最高法院\N{\fnarial\fs12\}that if we want to change the laws, we have to change the Supreme Court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.17,1:27:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}唐纳德•特朗普在纽约与福音派教徒骨干私下会面{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Donald Trump meeting privately in New York with leading evangelicals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.39,1:27:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}唐纳德•特朗普来了，进行了一次谈话{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Donald Trump came and had a conversation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.23,1:27:15.22,自定义,,0,0,0,,托尼•帕金斯    家庭研究协会主席
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.54,1:27:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在我们在任何事情上都没有一致{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Now we don't agree on everything{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.33,1:27:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,多年来，我一直致力于全国大选\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I've been working on national elections for a number of years{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.21,1:27:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,并且一直在努力巩固保守的福音派信徒\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and there's always been an effort to try to consolidate conservative evangelicals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.52,1:27:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对于任何共和党候选人来说，这都是一个关键的投票区{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is a critical voting block for any Republican candidate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.50,1:27:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要想在11月赢得大选，特朗普需要75%{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}To win in November, Donald Trump needs 75,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.81,1:27:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}甚至80%的福音派教徒{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}maybe even 80 percent of evangelicals{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.49,1:27:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的目标很简单\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Our goals are very simple{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.75,1:27:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这是为了增进我们对公共政策和整个文化的信仰\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is to advance faith in public policy and in our culture as a whole,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.97,1:27:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,从基督教的世界观的角度来说\N{\fnarial\fs12\}from a Christian world view{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.23,1:27:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是绝对的基督徒\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We are unapologetically Christian{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.08,1:27:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}福音派一直受到奥巴马政府的打击{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Evangelicals have been under constant attack by the Obama administration{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.25,1:27:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}坦白地说，他们已经厌倦了{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And quite frankly, they're tired of it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.38,1:27:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在奥巴马的领导下，政府采取了强硬手段\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And under Barack Obama, this heavy hand of government tried{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.84,1:27:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,试图迫使社会接受堕胎，和重新定义婚姻等问题\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to force society to accept things like abortion and the redefinition of marriage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.20,1:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这些事情与自然背道而驰\N{\fnarial\fs12\}These things run counter to nature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.52,1:28:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,它们违背了上帝的道德法则，所以是肉眼可见的倒退\N{\fnarial\fs12\}They run counter to the moral law of God. And so what you saw is pushback{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.56,1:28:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,显然，这里没有太多选择\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Obviously, there's not many choices here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.33,1:28:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,选择是在跟希拉里•克林顿之间\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The choice is between Hillary Clinton,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.98,1:28:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们知道她将为美国带来什么\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and we know exactly what she will provide to America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.75,1:28:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,或者还是唐纳德•特朗普\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Or we have Donald Trump{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.57,1:28:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他被认为是最不虔诚的候选人{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}He's considered the least religious of the candidates{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.20,1:28:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果伊万卡不是我女儿，也许我会和她约会{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If Ivanka weren't my daughter, perhaps I'd be dating her{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.29,1:28:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你知道性侵犯者之类的事{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You know about sexual predators and things like that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.92,1:28:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 你是之一！\N- 好吧，我不会那样说的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}- You are one!  - All right, wasn't gonna say that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.84,1:28:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我很赞成亲选择派，我只是相信选择{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I'm very pro-choice. I just believe in choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.75,1:28:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}福音派基督徒还没有完全同意{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Evangelical Christians aren't fully on board yet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.37,1:28:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有些人说，他们可能会在11月回家{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Some say they may sit home come November{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.17,1:28:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能忽视这个选区\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You cannot ignore this constituency{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.80,1:28:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但请记住，老布什是从亲选择派\N{\fnarial\fs12\}But remember, George H•W•Bush was pro-choice,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.16,1:28:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,变成了亲生命派的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}became pro-life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.49,1:28:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}布什先生有一些值得思考{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Mr. Bush has something to think about{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.48,1:28:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人的生命是宝贵的，已出生或未出生的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Human life is precious, born or unborn{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.24,1:28:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,罗纳德•里根在60年代末签署了美国最自由的堕胎法\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Ronald Reagan signed the most liberal abortion law in America in the late '60s,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.06,1:28:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,到了1980年，他成了反堕胎的英雄\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and was a pro-life hero by 1980{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.25,1:28:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为，当你中断怀孕时，你正在剥夺一个人的生命{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I think when you interrupt the pregnancy, you're taking a human life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.16,1:29:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,所以唐纳德•特朗普要做的就是，像之前那些候选人一样\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So all Donald Trump has to do is, as those prior nominees did,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.56,1:29:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,弄清楚…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}make it clear…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.48,1:29:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们一起参加了一场的全国性运动{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}We came together in a national crusade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.68,1:29:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}旨在让美国再次伟大{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}to make America great again{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.92,1:29:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并且要有一个新的开始{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And to make a new beginning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.87,1:29:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,弄清楚，“我改变了我的观念”\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Make it clear, "I changed my views"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.52,1:29:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我将要任命的法官，将会是亲生命派的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The justices that I'm going to appoint will be pro-life{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.33,1:29:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲生命派的选民对共和党的胜利绝对至关重要{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}The pro-life constituency is absolutely essential for a Republican victory{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.50,1:29:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}唐纳德•J•特朗普{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Donald J. Trump{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.05,1:29:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,要弄清楚，如果他成为总统，他将为这些事情而奋斗\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Make it clear that if he becomes president, he'll fight for those things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.96,1:29:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这不仅仅是关于“罗诉韦德案”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's not only about Roe v. Wade{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.18,1:29:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是关于美国正在发生的事情{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It is about what's happening right now in America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.65,1:29:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很多州都在{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}So many states are putting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.84,1:29:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对妇女实施非常严格的规定{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}very stringent regulations on women that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.46,1:29:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}阻止她们做出这种选择…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}block them from exercising that choice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.90,1:29:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信，让唐纳德•特朗普赢得亲生命团体支持的\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe what sold the pro-life community on Donald Trump{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.61,1:29:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这是在拉斯维加斯的最后一场辩论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}was the final debate in Las Vegas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.66,1:29:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我将捍卫“罗诉韦德案”{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I will defend Roe v. Wade,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.89,1:30:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我将捍卫妇女为自己健康做决定的权利{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}and I will defend women's rights to make their own health care decisions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.52,1:30:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我在观众席中，我在看着他…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I was in the audience. I was watching him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.98,1:30:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你们的分歧——一个女人堕胎的权利？{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}…which divides you-- a woman's right to abortion?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.81,1:30:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,当他开始进入讨论\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when he went into a discussion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.08,1:30:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,分期堕胎，晚期堕胎…\N{\fnarial\fs12\}of partial-birth abortion, late-term abortion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.78,1:30:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果按照希拉里的说法，在第9个月{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}If you go with what Hillary is saying, in the ninth month,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.98,1:30:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你可以把婴儿从母亲的子宫里扯出来…{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}you can take the baby and rip the baby out of the womb of the mother….{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.37,1:30:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道那些是唐纳德•特朗普的话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I knew those were Donald Trump's words{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.19,1:30:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在，你可以说这没问题{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Now, you can say that that's okay{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.96,1:30:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是一些演讲稿撰写人的原话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Those were not the words of some speechwriter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.93,1:30:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说这不太好\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It's not okay with me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.78,1:30:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为根据她所说的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}Because based on what she's saying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.58,1:30:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,很明显，是特朗普自己当时在说这话\N{\fnarial\fs12\}It was clearly Trump speaking at that moment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.67,1:30:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你可以把婴儿从子宫里取出来，在第9个月{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}You can take the baby and rip the baby out of the womb, in the ninth month,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.89,1:30:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在最后一天！这是不可接受的{\i0}\N{\fnarial\fs12\}on the final day! And that's not acceptable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.00,1:30:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当他这么做的时候\N{\fnarial\fs12\}And when he did that,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.80,1:30:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信他与全国各地的亲生命派达成了协议\N{\fnarial\fs12\}I believe he sealed the deal with pro-lifers across the country{\r}
